00494 /* -------- AIC_SMR[32] : (AIC Offset: 0x00) Source Mode Register -------- */
00495 #define AIC_SMR_PRIOR_Pos 0
00496 #define AIC_SMR_PRIOR_Msk (0x7u << AIC_SMR_PRIOR_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Priority Level */
00497 #define   AIC_SMR_PRIOR_LOWEST (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Lowest priority for the corresponding interrupt */
00498 #define   AIC_SMR_PRIOR_HIGHEST (0x7u << 0) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Highest priority for the corresponding interrupt */
00499 #define AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_Pos 5
00500 #define AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_Msk (0x3u << AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Interrupt Source Type */
00501 #define   AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_INT_LEVEL_SENSITIVE (0x0u << 5) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) High level Sensitive for internal sourceLow level Sensitive for external source */
00502 #define   AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_INT_EDGE_TRIGGERED (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Positive edge triggered for internal sourceNegative edge triggered for external source */
00503 #define   AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_EXT_HIGH_LEVEL (0x2u << 5) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) High level Sensitive for internal sourceHigh level Sensitive for external source */
00504 #define   AIC_SMR_SRCTYPE_EXT_POSITIVE_EDGE (0x3u << 5) /**< \brief (AIC_SMR[32]) Positive edge triggered for internal sourcePositive edge triggered for external source */
00505 /* -------- AIC_SVR[32] : (AIC Offset: 0x80) Source Vector Register -------- */
00506 #define AIC_SVR_VECTOR_Pos 0
00507 #define AIC_SVR_VECTOR_Msk (0xffffffffu << AIC_SVR_VECTOR_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_SVR[32]) Source Vector */
00508 #define AIC_SVR_VECTOR(value) ((AIC_SVR_VECTOR_Msk & ((value) << AIC_SVR_VECTOR_Pos)))
00509 /* -------- AIC_IVR : (AIC Offset: 0x100) Interrupt Vector Register -------- */
00510 #define AIC_IVR_IRQV_Pos 0
00511 #define AIC_IVR_IRQV_Msk (0xffffffffu << AIC_IVR_IRQV_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_IVR) Interrupt Vector Register */
00512 /* -------- AIC_FVR : (AIC Offset: 0x104) FIQ Interrupt Vector Register -------- */
00513 #define AIC_FVR_FIQV_Pos 0
00514 #define AIC_FVR_FIQV_Msk (0xffffffffu << AIC_FVR_FIQV_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_FVR) FIQ Vector Register */
00515 /* -------- AIC_ISR : (AIC Offset: 0x108) Interrupt Status Register -------- */
00516 #define AIC_ISR_IRQID_Pos 0
00517 #define AIC_ISR_IRQID_Msk (0x1fu << AIC_ISR_IRQID_Pos) /**< \brief (AIC_ISR) Current Interrupt Identifier */

00841 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
00842 /** \brief Dbgu hardware registers */
00843 typedef struct {
00844   WoReg DBGU_CR;      /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0000) Control Register */
00845   RwReg DBGU_MR;      /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register */
00846   WoReg DBGU_IER;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register */
00847   WoReg DBGU_IDR;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register */
00848   RoReg DBGU_IMR;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0010) Interrupt Mask Register */
00849   RoReg DBGU_SR;      /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0014) Status Register */
00850   RoReg DBGU_RHR;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0018) Receive Holding Register */
00851   WoReg DBGU_THR;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x001C) Transmit Holding Register */
00852   RwReg DBGU_BRGR;    /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0020) Baud Rate Generator Register */
00853   RoReg Reserved1[7];
00854   RoReg DBGU_CIDR;    /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0040) Chip ID Register */
00855   RoReg DBGU_EXID;    /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0044) Chip ID Extension Register */
00856   RwReg DBGU_FNR;     /**< \brief (Dbgu Offset: 0x0048) Force NTRST Register */
00857 } Dbgu;
00858 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
00859 /* -------- DBGU_CR : (DBGU Offset: 0x0000) Control Register -------- */
00860 #define DBGU_CR_RSTRX (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Reset Receiver */
00861 #define DBGU_CR_RSTTX (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Reset Transmitter */
00862 #define DBGU_CR_RXEN (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Receiver Enable */
00863 #define DBGU_CR_RXDIS (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Receiver Disable */
00864 #define DBGU_CR_TXEN (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Transmitter Enable */
00865 #define DBGU_CR_TXDIS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Transmitter Disable */
00866 #define DBGU_CR_RSTSTA (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (DBGU_CR) Reset Status Bits */
00867 /* -------- DBGU_MR : (DBGU Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register -------- */
00868 #define DBGU_MR_PAR_Pos 9
00869 #define DBGU_MR_PAR_Msk (0x7u << DBGU_MR_PAR_Pos) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Parity Type */
00870 #define   DBGU_MR_PAR_EVEN (0x0u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Even Parity */
00871 #define   DBGU_MR_PAR_ODD (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Odd Parity */
00872 #define   DBGU_MR_PAR_SPACE (0x2u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Space: Parity forced to 0 */
00873 #define   DBGU_MR_PAR_MARK (0x3u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Mark: Parity forced to 1 */
00874 #define   DBGU_MR_PAR_NONE (0x4u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) No Parity */
00875 #define DBGU_MR_CHMODE_Pos 14
00876 #define DBGU_MR_CHMODE_Msk (0x3u << DBGU_MR_CHMODE_Pos) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Channel Mode */
00877 #define   DBGU_MR_CHMODE_NORM (0x0u << 14) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Normal Mode */
00878 #define   DBGU_MR_CHMODE_AUTO (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Automatic Echo */
00879 #define   DBGU_MR_CHMODE_LOCLOOP (0x2u << 14) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Local Loopback */
00880 #define   DBGU_MR_CHMODE_REMLOOP (0x3u << 14) /**< \brief (DBGU_MR) Remote Loopback */
00881 /* -------- DBGU_IER : (DBGU Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
00882 #define DBGU_IER_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable RXRDY Interrupt */
00883 #define DBGU_IER_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable TXRDY Interrupt */

00886 #define DBGU_IER_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable Parity Error Interrupt */
00887 #define DBGU_IER_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable TXEMPTY Interrupt */
00888 #define DBGU_IER_COMMTX (0x1u << 30) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable COMMTX (from ARM) Interrupt */
00889 #define DBGU_IER_COMMRX (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (DBGU_IER) Enable COMMRX (from ARM) Interrupt */
00890 /* -------- DBGU_IDR : (DBGU Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
00891 #define DBGU_IDR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DBGU_IDR) Disable RXRDY Interrupt */

00898 #define DBGU_IDR_COMMRX (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (DBGU_IDR) Disable COMMRX (from ARM) Interrupt */
00899 /* -------- DBGU_IMR : (DBGU Offset: 0x0010) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
00900 #define DBGU_IMR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DBGU_IMR) Mask RXRDY Interrupt */

01035 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR DDR_SDR SDRAM Controller */

01039 
01040 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
01041 /** \brief Ddrsdrc hardware registers */
01042 typedef struct {
01043   RwReg DDRSDRC_MR;    /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x00) DDRSDRC Mode Register */
01044   RwReg DDRSDRC_RTR;   /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x04) DDRSDRC Refresh Timer Register */
01045   RwReg DDRSDRC_CR;    /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x08) DDRSDRC Configuration Register */
01046   RwReg DDRSDRC_TPR0;  /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x0C) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 0 Register */
01047   RwReg DDRSDRC_TPR1;  /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x10) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 1 Register */
01048   RwReg DDRSDRC_TPR2;  /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x14) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 2 Register */
01049   RoReg Reserved1[1];
01050   RwReg DDRSDRC_LPR;   /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x1C) DDRSDRC Low-power Register */
01051   RwReg DDRSDRC_MD;    /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x20) DDRSDRC Memory Device Register */
01052   RoReg DDRSDRC_DLL;   /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x24) DDRSDRC DLL Information Register */
01053   RoReg Reserved2[1];
01054   RwReg DDRSDRC_HS;    /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0x2C) DDRSDRC High Speed Register */
01055   RoReg Reserved3[45];
01056   RwReg DDRSDRC_WPMR;  /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0xE4) DDRSDRC Write Protect Mode Register */
01057   RoReg DDRSDRC_WPSR;  /**< \brief (Ddrsdrc Offset: 0xE8) DDRSDRC Write Protect Status Register */
01058 } Ddrsdrc;
01059 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
01060 /* -------- DDRSDRC_MR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x00) DDRSDRC Mode Register -------- */
01061 #define DDRSDRC_MR_MODE_Pos 0
01062 #define DDRSDRC_MR_MODE_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_MR_MODE_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_MR) DDRSDRC Command Mode */
01063 #define DDRSDRC_MR_MODE(value) ((DDRSDRC_MR_MODE_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_MR_MODE_Pos)))
01064 /* -------- DDRSDRC_RTR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x04) DDRSDRC Refresh Timer Register -------- */
01065 #define DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT_Pos 0
01066 #define DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT_Msk (0xfffu << DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_RTR) DDRSDRC Refresh Timer Count */
01067 #define DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT(value) ((DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_RTR_COUNT_Pos)))
01068 /* -------- DDRSDRC_CR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x08) DDRSDRC Configuration Register -------- */
01069 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NC_Pos 0
01070 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NC_Msk (0x3u << DDRSDRC_CR_NC_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Number of Column Bits */
01071 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NC(value) ((DDRSDRC_CR_NC_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_CR_NC_Pos)))
01072 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NR_Pos 2
01073 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NR_Msk (0x3u << DDRSDRC_CR_NR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Number of Row Bits */
01074 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NR(value) ((DDRSDRC_CR_NR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_CR_NR_Pos)))
01075 #define DDRSDRC_CR_CAS_Pos 4
01076 #define DDRSDRC_CR_CAS_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_CR_CAS_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) CAS Latency */
01077 #define DDRSDRC_CR_CAS(value) ((DDRSDRC_CR_CAS_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_CR_CAS_Pos)))
01078 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DLL (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Reset DLL */
01079 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DIC (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Output Driver Impedance Control */
01080 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DS (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Output Driver Impedance Control */
01081 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DIS_DLL (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Disable DLL */
01082 #define DDRSDRC_CR_OCD_Pos 12
01083 #define DDRSDRC_CR_OCD_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_CR_OCD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Off-chip Driver */
01084 #define DDRSDRC_CR_OCD(value) ((DDRSDRC_CR_OCD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_CR_OCD_Pos)))
01085 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DQMS (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Mask Data is Shared */
01086 #define DDRSDRC_CR_ACTBST (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) ACTIVE Bank X to Burst Stop Read Access Bank Y */
01087 #define DDRSDRC_CR_NB (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Number of Banks */
01088 #define DDRSDRC_CR_DECOD (0x1u << 22) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_CR) Type of Decoding */
01089 /* -------- DDRSDRC_TPR0 : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x0C) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 0 Register -------- */
01090 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS_Pos 0
01091 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Active to Precharge Delay */
01092 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRAS_Pos)))
01093 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD_Pos 4
01094 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Row to Column Delay */
01095 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRCD_Pos)))
01096 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR_Pos 8
01097 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Write Recovery Delay */
01098 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWR_Pos)))
01099 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC_Pos 12
01100 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Row Cycle Delay */
01101 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRC_Pos)))
01102 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP_Pos 16
01103 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Row Precharge Delay */
01104 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRP_Pos)))
01105 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD_Pos 20
01106 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0)  */
01107 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TRRD_Pos)))
01108 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR_Pos 24
01109 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Internal Write to Read Delay */
01110 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TWTR_Pos)))
01111 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_REDUCE_WRRD (0x1u << 27) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0)  */
01112 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD_Pos 28
01113 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR0) Load Mode Register Command to Active or Refresh Command */
01114 #define DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR0_TMRD_Pos)))
01115 /* -------- DDRSDRC_TPR1 : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x10) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 1 Register -------- */
01116 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC_Pos 0
01117 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC_Msk (0x1fu << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR1) Row Cycle Delay */
01118 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TRFC_Pos)))
01119 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR_Pos 8
01120 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR_Msk (0xffu << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR1) Exit Self Refresh Delay to Non-read Command */
01121 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSNR_Pos)))
01122 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD_Pos 16
01123 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD_Msk (0xffu << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR1) ExiT Self Refresh Delay to Read Command */
01124 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXSRD_Pos)))
01125 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP_Pos 24
01126 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR1) Exit Power-down Delay to First Command */
01127 #define DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR1_TXP_Pos)))
01128 /* -------- DDRSDRC_TPR2 : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x14) DDRSDRC Timing Parameter 2 Register -------- */
01129 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD_Pos 0
01130 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR2) Exit Active Power Down Delay to Read Command in Mode "Fast Exit". */
01131 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARD_Pos)))
01132 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS_Pos 4
01133 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR2) Exit Active Power Down Delay to Read Command in Mode "Slow Exit". */
01134 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TXARDS_Pos)))
01135 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA_Pos 8
01136 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR2) Row Precharge All Delay */
01137 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRPA_Pos)))
01138 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP_Pos 12
01139 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR2) Read to Precharge */
01140 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TRTP_Pos)))
01141 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW_Pos 16
01142 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW_Msk (0xfu << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_TPR2) Four Active window */
01143 #define DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW(value) ((DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_TPR2_TFAW_Pos)))
01144 /* -------- DDRSDRC_LPR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x1C) DDRSDRC Low-power Register -------- */
01145 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB_Pos 0
01146 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB_Msk (0x3u << DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Low-power Command Bit */
01147 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB(value) ((DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_LPR_LPCB_Pos)))
01148 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_CLK_FR (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Clock Frozen Command Bit */
01149 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR_Pos 4
01150 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Partial Array Self Refresh */
01151 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR(value) ((DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_LPR_PASR_Pos)))
01152 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_DS_Pos 8
01153 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_DS_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_LPR_DS_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Drive Strength */
01154 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_DS(value) ((DDRSDRC_LPR_DS_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_LPR_DS_Pos)))
01155 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT_Pos 12
01156 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT_Msk (0x3u << DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR)  */
01157 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT(value) ((DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_LPR_TIMEOUT_Pos)))
01158 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_APDE (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Active Power Down Exit Time */
01159 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR_Pos 20
01160 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR_Msk (0x3u << DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_LPR) Update Load Mode Register and Extended Mode Register */
01161 #define DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR(value) ((DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_LPR_UPD_MR_Pos)))
01162 /* -------- DDRSDRC_MD : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x20) DDRSDRC Memory Device Register -------- */
01163 #define DDRSDRC_MD_MD_Pos 0
01164 #define DDRSDRC_MD_MD_Msk (0x7u << DDRSDRC_MD_MD_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_MD) Memory Device */
01165 #define DDRSDRC_MD_MD(value) ((DDRSDRC_MD_MD_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_MD_MD_Pos)))
01166 #define DDRSDRC_MD_DBW (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_MD) Data Bus Width */
01167 /* -------- DDRSDRC_DLL : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x24) DDRSDRC DLL Information Register -------- */
01168 #define DDRSDRC_DLL_MDINC (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_DLL) DLL Master Delay Increment */
01169 #define DDRSDRC_DLL_MDDEC (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_DLL) DLL Master Delay Decrement */
01170 #define DDRSDRC_DLL_MDOVF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_DLL) DLL Master Delay Overflow Flag */
01171 #define DDRSDRC_DLL_MDVAL_Pos 8
01172 #define DDRSDRC_DLL_MDVAL_Msk (0xffu << DDRSDRC_DLL_MDVAL_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_DLL) DLL Master Delay Value */
01173 /* -------- DDRSDRC_HS : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0x2C) DDRSDRC High Speed Register -------- */
01174 #define DDRSDRC_HS_DIS_ANTICIP_READ (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_HS)  */
01175 /* -------- DDRSDRC_WPMR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0xE4) DDRSDRC Write Protect Mode Register -------- */
01176 #define DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_WPMR) Write Protect Enable */
01177 #define DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos 8
01178 #define DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk (0xffffffu << DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_WPMR) Write Protect KEY */
01179 #define DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY(value) ((DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk & ((value) << DDRSDRC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos)))
01180 /* -------- DDRSDRC_WPSR : (DDRSDRC Offset: 0xE8) DDRSDRC Write Protect Status Register -------- */
01181 #define DDRSDRC_WPSR_WPVS (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_WPSR) Write Protect Violation Status */
01182 #define DDRSDRC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos 8
01183 #define DDRSDRC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Msk (0xffffu << DDRSDRC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos) /**< \brief (DDRSDRC_WPSR) Write Protect Violation Source */
01184 
01185 /*@}*/

01579 #define   DMAC_CFG_LOCK_B_DISABLE (0x0u << 21) /**< \brief (DMAC_CFG) AHB Bus Locking capability is disabled. */

01585 #define DMAC_CFG_AHB_PROT(value) ((DMAC_CFG_AHB_PROT_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_CFG_AHB_PROT_Pos)))
01586 #define DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_Pos 28
01587 #define DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_Msk (0x3u << DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_CFG) FIFO Configuration */
01588 #define   DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_ALAP_CFG (0x0u << 28) /**< \brief (DMAC_CFG) The largest defined length AHB burst is performed on the destination AHB interface. */
01589 #define   DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_HALF_CFG (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (DMAC_CFG) When half FIFO size is available/filled, a source/destination request is serviced. */
01590 #define   DMAC_CFG_FIFOCFG_ASAP_CFG (0x2u << 28) /**< \brief (DMAC_CFG) When there is enough space/data available to perform a single AHB access, then the request is serviced. */
01591 /* -------- DMAC_SPIP : (DMAC Offset: N/A) DMAC Channel Source Picture-in-Picture Configuration Register -------- */
01592 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE_Pos 0
01593 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE_Msk (0xffffu << DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_SPIP) Source Picture-in-Picture Hole */
01594 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE(value) ((DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_HOLE_Pos)))
01595 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos 16
01596 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY_Msk (0x3ffu << DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_SPIP) Source Picture-in-Picture Boundary */
01597 #define DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY(value) ((DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_SPIP_SPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos)))
01598 /* -------- DMAC_DPIP : (DMAC Offset: N/A) DMAC Channel Destination Picture-in-Picture Configuration Register -------- */
01599 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE_Pos 0
01600 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE_Msk (0xffffu << DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_DPIP) Destination Picture-in-Picture Hole */
01601 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE(value) ((DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_HOLE_Pos)))
01602 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos 16
01603 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY_Msk (0x3ffu << DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_DPIP) Destination Picture-in-Picture Boundary */
01604 #define DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY(value) ((DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_DPIP_DPIP_BOUNDARY_Pos)))
01605 /* -------- DMAC_WPMR : (DMAC Offset: 0x1E4) DMAC Write Protect Mode Register -------- */
01606 #define DMAC_WPMR_WPEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DMAC_WPMR) Write Protect Enable */
01607 #define DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos 8
01608 #define DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk (0xffffffu << DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_WPMR) Write Protect KEY */
01609 #define DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY(value) ((DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk & ((value) << DMAC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos)))
01610 /* -------- DMAC_WPSR : (DMAC Offset: 0x1E8) DMAC Write Protect Status Register -------- */
01611 #define DMAC_WPSR_WPVS (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (DMAC_WPSR) Write Protect Violation Status */
01612 #define DMAC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos 8
01613 #define DMAC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Msk (0xffffu << DMAC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos) /**< \brief (DMAC_WPSR) Write Protect Violation Source */

01657 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
01658 /** \brief Hsmci hardware registers */
01659 typedef struct {
01660   WoReg HSMCI_CR;        /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x00) Control Register */

01665   WoReg HSMCI_CMDR;      /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x14) Command Register */

01669   RoReg HSMCI_RDR;       /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x30) Receive Data Register */

01673   WoReg HSMCI_IER;       /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x44) Interrupt Enable Register */
01674   WoReg HSMCI_IDR;       /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x48) Interrupt Disable Register */
01675   RoReg HSMCI_IMR;       /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x4C) Interrupt Mask Register */
01676   RwReg HSMCI_DMA;       /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0x50) DMA Configuration Register */

01680   RoReg HSMCI_WPSR;      /**< \brief (Hsmci Offset: 0xE8) Write Protection Status Register */

01685 /* -------- HSMCI_CR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
01686 #define HSMCI_CR_MCIEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CR) Multi-Media Interface Enable */
01687 #define HSMCI_CR_MCIDIS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CR) Multi-Media Interface Disable */
01688 #define HSMCI_CR_PWSEN (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CR) Power Save Mode Enable */
01689 #define HSMCI_CR_PWSDIS (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CR) Power Save Mode Disable */
01690 #define HSMCI_CR_SWRST (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CR) Software Reset */
01691 /* -------- HSMCI_MR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x04) Mode Register -------- */
01692 #define HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV_Pos 0
01693 #define HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV_Msk (0xffu << HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR) Clock Divider */
01694 #define HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV(value) ((HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_MR_CLKDIV_Pos)))
01695 #define HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV_Pos 8
01696 #define HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV_Msk (0x7u << HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR) Power Saving Divider */
01697 #define HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV(value) ((HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_MR_PWSDIV_Pos)))
01698 #define HSMCI_MR_RDPROOF (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR)  */
01699 #define HSMCI_MR_WRPROOF (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR)  */
01700 #define HSMCI_MR_FBYTE (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR) Force Byte Transfer */
01701 #define HSMCI_MR_PADV (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR) Padding Value */
01702 #define HSMCI_MR_CLKODD (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (HSMCI_MR) Clock divider is odd */
01703 /* -------- HSMCI_DTOR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x08) Data Timeout Register -------- */
01704 #define HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC_Pos 0
01705 #define HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC_Msk (0xfu << HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) Data Timeout Cycle Number */
01706 #define HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC(value) ((HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_DTOR_DTOCYC_Pos)))
01707 #define HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_Pos 4
01708 #define HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_Msk (0x7u << HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) Data Timeout Multiplier */
01709 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_1 (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC */
01710 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_16 (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 16 */
01711 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_128 (0x2u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 128 */
01712 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_256 (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 256 */
01713 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_1024 (0x4u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 1024 */
01714 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_4096 (0x5u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 4096 */
01715 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_65536 (0x6u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 65536 */
01716 #define   HSMCI_DTOR_DTOMUL_1048576 (0x7u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DTOR) DTOCYC x 1048576 */
01717 /* -------- HSMCI_SDCR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x0C) SD/SDIO Card Register -------- */
01718 #define HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_Pos 0
01719 #define HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) SDCard/SDIO Slot */
01720 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_SLOTA (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) Slot A is selected. */
01721 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_SLOTB (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) - */
01722 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_SLOTC (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) - */
01723 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCSEL_SLOTD (0x3u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) - */
01724 #define HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_Pos 6
01725 #define HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) SDCard/SDIO Bus Width */
01726 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_1 (0x0u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) 1 bit */
01727 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_4 (0x2u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) 4 bit */
01728 #define   HSMCI_SDCR_SDCBUS_8 (0x3u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_SDCR) 8 bit */
01729 /* -------- HSMCI_ARGR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x10) Argument Register -------- */
01730 #define HSMCI_ARGR_ARG_Pos 0
01731 #define HSMCI_ARGR_ARG_Msk (0xffffffffu << HSMCI_ARGR_ARG_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_ARGR) Command Argument */
01732 #define HSMCI_ARGR_ARG(value) ((HSMCI_ARGR_ARG_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_ARGR_ARG_Pos)))
01733 /* -------- HSMCI_CMDR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x14) Command Register -------- */
01734 #define HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB_Pos 0
01735 #define HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB_Msk (0x3fu << HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Command Number */
01736 #define HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB(value) ((HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_CMDR_CMDNB_Pos)))
01737 #define HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_Pos 6
01738 #define HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Response Type */
01739 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_NORESP (0x0u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) No response. */
01740 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_48_BIT (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) 48-bit response. */
01741 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_136_BIT (0x2u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) 136-bit response. */
01742 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_RSPTYP_R1B (0x3u << 6) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) R1b response type */
01743 #define HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_Pos 8
01744 #define HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_Msk (0x7u << HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Special Command */
01745 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_STD (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Not a special CMD. */
01746 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_INIT (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Initialization CMD: 74 clock cycles for initialization sequence. */
01747 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_SYNC (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Synchronized CMD: Wait for the end of the current data block transfer before sending the pending command. */
01748 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_CE_ATA (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) CE-ATA Completion Signal disable Command. The host cancels the ability for the device to return a command completion signal on the command line. */
01749 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_IT_CMD (0x4u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Interrupt command: Corresponds to the Interrupt Mode (CMD40). */
01750 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_IT_RESP (0x5u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Interrupt response: Corresponds to the Interrupt Mode (CMD40). */
01751 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_BOR (0x6u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Boot Operation Request. Start a boot operation mode, the host processor can read boot data from the MMC device directly. */
01752 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_SPCMD_EBO (0x7u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) End Boot Operation. This command allows the host processor to terminate the boot operation mode. */
01753 #define HSMCI_CMDR_OPDCMD (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Open Drain Command */
01754 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_OPDCMD_PUSHPULL (0x0u << 11) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Push pull command. */
01755 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_OPDCMD_OPENDRAIN (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Open drain command. */
01756 #define HSMCI_CMDR_MAXLAT (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Max Latency for Command to Response */
01757 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_MAXLAT_5 (0x0u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) 5-cycle max latency. */
01758 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_MAXLAT_64 (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) 64-cycle max latency. */
01759 #define HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_Pos 16
01760 #define HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Transfer Command */
01761 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_NO_DATA (0x0u << 16) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) No data transfer */
01762 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_START_DATA (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Start data transfer */
01763 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRCMD_STOP_DATA (0x2u << 16) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Stop data transfer */
01764 #define HSMCI_CMDR_TRDIR (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Transfer Direction */
01765 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRDIR_WRITE (0x0u << 18) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Write. */
01766 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRDIR_READ (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Read. */
01767 #define HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_Pos 19
01768 #define HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_Msk (0x7u << HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Transfer Type */
01769 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_SINGLE (0x0u << 19) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) MMC/SDCard Single Block */
01770 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_MULTIPLE (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) MMC/SDCard Multiple Block */
01771 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_STREAM (0x2u << 19) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) MMC Stream */
01772 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_BYTE (0x4u << 19) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) SDIO Byte */
01773 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_TRTYP_BLOCK (0x5u << 19) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) SDIO Block */
01774 #define HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_Pos 24
01775 #define HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) SDIO Special Command */
01776 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_STD (0x0u << 24) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Not an SDIO Special Command */
01777 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_SUSPEND (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) SDIO Suspend Command */
01778 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_IOSPCMD_RESUME (0x2u << 24) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) SDIO Resume Command */
01779 #define HSMCI_CMDR_ATACS (0x1u << 26) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) ATA with Command Completion Signal */
01780 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_ATACS_NORMAL (0x0u << 26) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Normal operation mode. */
01781 #define   HSMCI_CMDR_ATACS_COMPLETION (0x1u << 26) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) This bit indicates that a completion signal is expected within a programmed amount of time (HSMCI_CSTOR). */
01782 #define HSMCI_CMDR_BOOT_ACK (0x1u << 27) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CMDR) Boot Operation Acknowledge. */
01783 /* -------- HSMCI_BLKR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x18) Block Register -------- */
01784 #define HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_Pos 0
01785 #define HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_Msk (0xffffu << HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_BLKR) MMC/SDIO Block Count - SDIO Byte Count */
01786 #define   HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_MULTIPLE (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_BLKR) MMC/SDCARD Multiple BlockFrom 1 to 65635: Value 0 corresponds to an infinite block transfer. */
01787 #define   HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_BYTE (0x4u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_BLKR) SDIO ByteFrom 1 to 512 bytes: Value 0 corresponds to a 512-byte transfer.Values from 0x200 to 0xFFFF are forbidden. */
01788 #define   HSMCI_BLKR_BCNT_BLOCK (0x5u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_BLKR) SDIO BlockFrom 1 to 511 blocks: Value 0 corresponds to an infinite block transfer.Values from 0x200 to 0xFFFF are forbidden. */
01789 #define HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN_Pos 16
01790 #define HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN_Msk (0xffffu << HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_BLKR) Data Block Length */
01791 #define HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN(value) ((HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_BLKR_BLKLEN_Pos)))
01792 /* -------- HSMCI_CSTOR : (HSMCI Offset: 0x1C) Completion Signal Timeout Register -------- */
01793 #define HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC_Pos 0
01794 #define HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC_Msk (0xfu << HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) Completion Signal Timeout Cycle Number */
01795 #define HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC(value) ((HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOCYC_Pos)))
01796 #define HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_Pos 4
01797 #define HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_Msk (0x7u << HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) Completion Signal Timeout Multiplier */
01798 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_1 (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 1 */
01799 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_16 (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 16 */
01800 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_128 (0x2u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 128 */
01801 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_256 (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 256 */
01802 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_1024 (0x4u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 1024 */
01803 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_4096 (0x5u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 4096 */
01804 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_65536 (0x6u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 65536 */
01805 #define   HSMCI_CSTOR_CSTOMUL_1048576 (0x7u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CSTOR) CSTOCYC x 1048576 */

01919 #define HSMCI_IMR_UNRE (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (HSMCI_IMR) Underrun Interrupt Mask */
01920 /* -------- HSMCI_DMA : (HSMCI Offset: 0x50) DMA Configuration Register -------- */
01921 #define HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET_Pos 0
01922 #define HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) DMA Write Buffer Offset */
01923 #define HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET(value) ((HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_DMA_OFFSET_Pos)))
01924 #define HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_Pos 4
01925 #define HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_Msk (0x3u << HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) DMA Channel Read and Write Chunk Size */
01926 #define   HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_1 (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) 1 data available */
01927 #define   HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_4 (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) 4 data available */
01928 #define   HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_8 (0x2u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) 8 data available */
01929 #define   HSMCI_DMA_CHKSIZE_16 (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) 16 data available */
01930 #define HSMCI_DMA_DMAEN (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) DMA Hardware Handshaking Enable */
01931 #define HSMCI_DMA_ROPT (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_DMA) Read Optimization with padding */
01932 /* -------- HSMCI_CFG : (HSMCI Offset: 0x54) Configuration Register -------- */
01933 #define HSMCI_CFG_FIFOMODE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CFG) HSMCI Internal FIFO control mode */
01934 #define HSMCI_CFG_FERRCTRL (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CFG) Flow Error flag reset control mode */
01935 #define HSMCI_CFG_HSMODE (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CFG) High Speed Mode */
01936 #define HSMCI_CFG_LSYNC (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (HSMCI_CFG) Synchronize on the last block */
01937 /* -------- HSMCI_WPMR : (HSMCI Offset: 0xE4) Write Protection Mode Register -------- */
01938 #define HSMCI_WPMR_WP_EN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPMR) Write Protection Enable */
01939 #define HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY_Pos 8
01940 #define HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY_Msk (0xffffffu << HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPMR) Write Protection Key password */
01941 #define HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY(value) ((HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_WPMR_WP_KEY_Pos)))
01942 /* -------- HSMCI_WPSR : (HSMCI Offset: 0xE8) Write Protection Status Register -------- */
01943 #define HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_Pos 0
01944 #define HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_Msk (0xfu << HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) Write Protection Violation Status */
01945 #define   HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_NONE (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) No Write Protection Violation occurred since the last read of this register (WP_SR) */
01946 #define   HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_WRITE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) Write Protection detected unauthorized attempt to write a control register had occurred (since the last read.) */
01947 #define   HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_RESET (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) Software reset had been performed while Write Protection was enabled (since the last read). */
01948 #define   HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VS_BOTH (0x3u << 0) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) Both Write Protection violation and software reset with Write Protection enabled have occurred since the last read. */
01949 #define HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VSRC_Pos 8
01950 #define HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VSRC_Msk (0xffffu << HSMCI_WPSR_WP_VSRC_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_WPSR) Write Protection Violation SouRCe */
01951 /* -------- HSMCI_FIFO[256] : (HSMCI Offset: 0x200) FIFO Memory Aperture0 -------- */
01952 #define HSMCI_FIFO_DATA_Pos 0
01953 #define HSMCI_FIFO_DATA_Msk (0xffffffffu << HSMCI_FIFO_DATA_Pos) /**< \brief (HSMCI_FIFO[256]) Data to Read or Data to Write */
01954 #define HSMCI_FIFO_DATA(value) ((HSMCI_FIFO_DATA_Msk & ((value) << HSMCI_FIFO_DATA_Pos)))

04755 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
04756 /** \brief Pit hardware registers */
04757 typedef struct {
04758   RwReg PIT_MR;   /**< \brief (Pit Offset: 0x00) Mode Register */
04759   RoReg PIT_SR;   /**< \brief (Pit Offset: 0x04) Status Register */
04760   RoReg PIT_PIVR; /**< \brief (Pit Offset: 0x08) Periodic Interval Value Register */
04761   RoReg PIT_PIIR; /**< \brief (Pit Offset: 0x0C) Periodic Interval Image Register */
04762 } Pit;
04763 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
04764 /* -------- PIT_MR : (PIT Offset: 0x00) Mode Register -------- */
04765 #define PIT_MR_PIV_Pos 0
04766 #define PIT_MR_PIV_Msk (0xfffffu << PIT_MR_PIV_Pos) /**< \brief (PIT_MR) Periodic Interval Value */
04767 #define PIT_MR_PIV(value) ((PIT_MR_PIV_Msk & ((value) << PIT_MR_PIV_Pos)))
04768 #define PIT_MR_PITEN (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (PIT_MR) Period Interval Timer Enabled */
04769 #define PIT_MR_PITIEN (0x1u << 25) /**< \brief (PIT_MR) Periodic Interval Timer Interrupt Enable */
04770 /* -------- PIT_SR : (PIT Offset: 0x04) Status Register -------- */
04771 #define PIT_SR_PITS (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PIT_SR) Periodic Interval Timer Status */
04772 /* -------- PIT_PIVR : (PIT Offset: 0x08) Periodic Interval Value Register -------- */
04773 #define PIT_PIVR_CPIV_Pos 0
04774 #define PIT_PIVR_CPIV_Msk (0xfffffu << PIT_PIVR_CPIV_Pos) /**< \brief (PIT_PIVR) Current Periodic Interval Value */
04775 #define PIT_PIVR_PICNT_Pos 20
04776 #define PIT_PIVR_PICNT_Msk (0xfffu << PIT_PIVR_PICNT_Pos) /**< \brief (PIT_PIVR) Periodic Interval Counter */
04777 /* -------- PIT_PIIR : (PIT Offset: 0x0C) Periodic Interval Image Register -------- */
04778 #define PIT_PIIR_CPIV_Pos 0
04779 #define PIT_PIIR_CPIV_Msk (0xfffffu << PIT_PIIR_CPIV_Pos) /**< \brief (PIT_PIIR) Current Periodic Interval Value */
04780 #define PIT_PIIR_PICNT_Pos 20
04781 #define PIT_PIIR_PICNT_Msk (0xfffu << PIT_PIIR_PICNT_Pos) /**< \brief (PIT_PIIR) Periodic Interval Counter */

04800   RoReg PMC_PCSR;      /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x0018) Peripheral Clock Status Register */
04801   RwReg CKGR_UCKR;     /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x001C) UTMI Clock Register */
04802   RwReg CKGR_MOR;      /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x0020) Main Oscillator Register */

04808   RwReg PMC_USB;       /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x0038) USB Clock Register */
04809   RwReg PMC_SMD;       /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x003C) Soft Modem Clock Register */

04811   RoReg Reserved4[6];
04812   WoReg PMC_IER;       /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x0060) Interrupt Enable Register */
04813   WoReg PMC_IDR;       /**< \brief (Pmc Offset: 0x0064) Interrupt Disable Register */

04828 #define PMC_SCER_SMDCK (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (PMC_SCER) SMD Clock Enable */

04832 #define PMC_SCER_PCK1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (PMC_SCER) Programmable Clock 1 Output Enable */

04841 #define PMC_SCDR_PCK1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (PMC_SCDR) Programmable Clock 1 Output Disable */

04999 #define PMC_MCKR_MDIV_Pos 8

05003 #define   PMC_MCKR_MDIV_PCK_DIV4 (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (PMC_MCKR) Master Clock is Prescaler Output Clock divided by 4.SysClk DDR is equal to 2 x MCK. DDRCK is equal to MCK. */
05004 #define   PMC_MCKR_MDIV_PCK_DIV3 (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (PMC_MCKR) Master Clock is Prescaler Output Clock divided by 3.SysClk DDR is equal to 2 x MCK. DDRCK is equal to MCK. */

05104 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Error Corrected Code Controller */
05105 /* ============================================================================= */
05106 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_PMECC Error Corrected Code Controller */
05107 /*@{*/
05108 
05109 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
05110 /** \brief PmeccEcc hardware registers */
05111 typedef struct {
05112   RwReg     PMECC_ECC[11]; /**< \brief (PmeccEcc Offset: 0x0) PMECC ECC x Register */
05113   RoReg     Reserved1[5];
05114 } PmeccEcc;
05115 /** \brief PmeccRem hardware registers */
05116 typedef struct {
05117   RwReg     PMECC_REM[12]; /**< \brief (PmeccRem Offset: 0x0) PMECC REM x Register */
05118   RoReg     Reserved2[4];
05119 } PmeccRem;
05120 /** \brief Pmecc hardware registers */
05121 #define PMECCECC_NUMBER 8
05122 #define PMECCREM_NUMBER 8
05123 typedef struct {
05124   RwReg     PMECC_CFG;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000000) PMECC Configuration Register */
05125   RwReg     PMECC_SAREA;  /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000004) PMECC Spare Area Size Register */
05126   RwReg     PMECC_SADDR;  /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000008) PMECC Start Address Register */
05127   RwReg     PMECC_EADDR;  /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x0000000C) PMECC End Address Register */
05128   RwReg     PMECC_CLK;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000010) PMECC Clock Control Register */
05129   WoReg     PMECC_CTRL;   /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000014) PMECC Control Register */
05130   RoReg     PMECC_SR;     /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000018) PMECC Status Register */
05131   WoReg     PMECC_IER;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x0000001C) PMECC Interrupt Enable register */
05132   WoReg     PMECC_IDR;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000020) PMECC Interrupt Disable Register */
05133   RoReg     PMECC_IMR;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000024) PMECC Interrupt Mask Register */
05134   RoReg     PMECC_ISR;    /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x00000028) PMECC Interrupt Status Register */
05135   RoReg     Reserved1[5];
05136   PmeccEcc  PMECC_ECC[PMECCECC_NUMBER]; /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x40) sec_num = 0 .. 7 */
05137   PmeccRem  PMECC_REM[PMECCREM_NUMBER]; /**< \brief (Pmecc Offset: 0x240) sec_num = 0 .. 7 */
05138 } Pmecc;
05139 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
05140 /* -------- PMECC_CFG : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000000) PMECC Configuration Register -------- */
05141 #define PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_Pos 0
05142 #define PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_Msk (0x7u << PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) Error Correct Capability */
05143 #define   PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_BCH_ERR2 (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 2 errors */
05144 #define   PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_BCH_ERR4 (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 4 errors */
05145 #define   PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_BCH_ERR8 (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 8 errors */
05146 #define   PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_BCH_ERR12 (0x3u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 12 errors */
05147 #define   PMECC_CFG_BCH_ERR_BCH_ERR24 (0x4u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 24 errors */
05148 #define PMECC_CFG_SECTORSZ (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) Sector Size */
05149 #define PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_Pos 8
05150 #define PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_Msk (0x3u << PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) Number of Sectors in the Page */
05151 #define   PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_PAGESIZE_1SEC (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 1 sector for main area (512 or 1024 bytes) */
05152 #define   PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_PAGESIZE_2SEC (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 2 sectors for main area (1024 or 2048 bytes) */
05153 #define   PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_PAGESIZE_4SEC (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 4 sectors for main area (2048 or 4096 bytes) */
05154 #define   PMECC_CFG_PAGESIZE_PAGESIZE_8SEC (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) 8 errors for main area (4096 or 8192 bytes) */
05155 #define PMECC_CFG_NANDWR (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) NAND Write Access */
05156 #define PMECC_CFG_SPAREEN (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) Spare Enable */
05157 #define PMECC_CFG_AUTO (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (PMECC_CFG) Automatic Mode Enable */
05158 /* -------- PMECC_SAREA : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000004) PMECC Spare Area Size Register -------- */
05159 #define PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE_Pos 0
05160 #define PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE_Msk (0x1ffu << PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_SAREA) Spare Area Size */
05161 #define PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE(value) ((PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE_Msk & ((value) << PMECC_SAREA_SPARESIZE_Pos)))
05162 /* -------- PMECC_SADDR : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000008) PMECC Start Address Register -------- */
05163 #define PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR_Pos 0
05164 #define PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR_Msk (0x1ffu << PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_SADDR) ECC Area Start Address (byte oriented address) */
05165 #define PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR(value) ((PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR_Msk & ((value) << PMECC_SADDR_STARTADDR_Pos)))
05166 /* -------- PMECC_EADDR : (PMECC Offset: 0x0000000C) PMECC End Address Register -------- */
05167 #define PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR_Pos 0
05168 #define PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR_Msk (0x1ffu << PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_EADDR) ECC Area End Address (byte oriented address) */
05169 #define PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR(value) ((PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR_Msk & ((value) << PMECC_EADDR_ENDADDR_Pos)))
05170 /* -------- PMECC_CLK : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000010) PMECC Clock Control Register -------- */
05171 #define PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL_Pos 0
05172 #define PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL_Msk (0x7u << PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_CLK) Clock Control Register */
05173 #define PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL(value) ((PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL_Msk & ((value) << PMECC_CLK_CLKCTRL_Pos)))
05174 /* -------- PMECC_CTRL : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000014) PMECC Control Register -------- */
05175 #define PMECC_CTRL_RST (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_CTRL) Reset the PMECC Module */
05176 #define PMECC_CTRL_DATA (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (PMECC_CTRL) Start a Data Phase */
05177 #define PMECC_CTRL_USER (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (PMECC_CTRL) Start a User Mode Phase */
05178 #define PMECC_CTRL_ENABLE (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (PMECC_CTRL) PMECC Module Enable */
05179 #define PMECC_CTRL_DISABLE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (PMECC_CTRL) PMECC Module Disable */
05180 /* -------- PMECC_SR : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000018) PMECC Status Register -------- */
05181 #define PMECC_SR_BUSY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_SR) The Kernel of the PMECC is Busy */
05182 #define PMECC_SR_ENABLE (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (PMECC_SR) PMECC Module Status */
05183 /* -------- PMECC_IER : (PMECC Offset: 0x0000001C) PMECC Interrupt Enable register -------- */
05184 #define PMECC_IER_ERRIE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_IER) Error Interrupt Enable */
05185 /* -------- PMECC_IDR : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000020) PMECC Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
05186 #define PMECC_IDR_ERRID (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_IDR) Error Interrupt Disable */
05187 /* -------- PMECC_IMR : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000024) PMECC Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
05188 #define PMECC_IMR_ERRIM (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMECC_IMR) Error Interrupt Enable */
05189 /* -------- PMECC_ISR : (PMECC Offset: 0x00000028) PMECC Interrupt Status Register -------- */
05190 #define PMECC_ISR_ERRIS_Pos 0
05191 #define PMECC_ISR_ERRIS_Msk (0xffu << PMECC_ISR_ERRIS_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_ISR) Error Interrupt Status Register */
05192 /* -------- PMECC_ECC[11] : (PMECC Offset: N/A) PMECC ECC x Register -------- */
05193 #define PMECC_ECC_ECC_Pos 0
05194 #define PMECC_ECC_ECC_Msk (0xffffffffu << PMECC_ECC_ECC_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_ECC[11]) BCH Redundancy */
05195 /* -------- PMECC_REM[12] : (PMECC Offset: N/A) PMECC REM x Register -------- */
05196 #define PMECC_REM_REM2NP1_Pos 0
05197 #define PMECC_REM_REM2NP1_Msk (0x3fffu << PMECC_REM_REM2NP1_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_REM[12]) BCH Remainder 2 * N + 1 */
05198 #define PMECC_REM_REM2NP3_Pos 16
05199 #define PMECC_REM_REM2NP3_Msk (0x3fffu << PMECC_REM_REM2NP3_Pos) /**< \brief (PMECC_REM[12]) BCH Remainder 2 * N + 3 */
05200 
05201 /*@}*/

05238 /* -------- PMERRLOC_ELDIS : (PMERRLOC Offset: 0x00C) Error Location Disable Register -------- */

05246 /* -------- PMERRLOC_ELIMR : (PMERRLOC Offset: 0x01C) Error Location Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
05247 #define PMERRLOC_ELIMR_DONE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMERRLOC_ELIMR) Computation Terminated Interrupt Mask */
05248 /* -------- PMERRLOC_ELISR : (PMERRLOC Offset: 0x020) Error Location Interrupt Status Register -------- */
05249 #define PMERRLOC_ELISR_DONE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (PMERRLOC_ELISR) Computation Terminated Interrupt Status */
05250 #define PMERRLOC_ELISR_ERR_CNT_Pos 8
05251 #define PMERRLOC_ELISR_ERR_CNT_Msk (0x1fu << PMERRLOC_ELISR_ERR_CNT_Pos) /**< \brief (PMERRLOC_ELISR) Error Counter value */
05252 /* -------- PMERRLOC_SIGMA[25] : (PMERRLOC Offset: 0x028) PMECC SIGMA 0 Register -------- */
05253 #define PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN_Pos 0
05254 #define PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN_Msk (0x3fffu << PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN_Pos) /**< \brief (PMERRLOC_SIGMA[25])  */
05255 #define PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN(value) ((PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN_Msk & ((value) << PMERRLOC_SIGMA_SIGMAN_Pos)))
05256 /* -------- PMERRLOC_EL[24] : (PMERRLOC Offset: 0x08C) PMECC Error Location 0 Register -------- */
05257 #define PMERRLOC_EL_ERRLOCN_Pos 0
05258 #define PMERRLOC_EL_ERRLOCN_Msk (0x3fffu << PMERRLOC_EL_ERRLOCN_Pos) /**< \brief (PMERRLOC_EL[24]) Error Position within the set {sector area, spare area}. */

05303 #define   PWM_MR_PREA_MCKDIV8 (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (PWM_MR) Master Clock divided by 8 */

05311 #define PWM_MR_DIVB_Pos 16

05375 #define   PWM_CMR_CPRE_MCKDIV512 (0x9u << 0) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Master Clock divided by 512 */
05376 #define   PWM_CMR_CPRE_MCKDIV1024 (0xAu << 0) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Master Clock divided by 1024 */
05377 #define   PWM_CMR_CPRE_CLKA (0xBu << 0) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Clock A */
05378 #define   PWM_CMR_CPRE_CLKB (0xCu << 0) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Clock B */
05379 #define PWM_CMR_CALG (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Channel Alignment */
05380 #define PWM_CMR_CPOL (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Channel Polarity */
05381 #define PWM_CMR_CPD (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (PWM_CMR) Channel Update Period */
05382 /* -------- PWM_CDTY : (PWM Offset: N/A) PWM Channel Duty Cycle Register -------- */
05383 #define PWM_CDTY_CDTY_Pos 0
05384 #define PWM_CDTY_CDTY_Msk (0xffffffffu << PWM_CDTY_CDTY_Pos) /**< \brief (PWM_CDTY) Channel Duty Cycle */
05385 #define PWM_CDTY_CDTY(value) ((PWM_CDTY_CDTY_Msk & ((value) << PWM_CDTY_CDTY_Pos)))
05386 /* -------- PWM_CPRD : (PWM Offset: N/A) PWM Channel Period Register -------- */
05387 #define PWM_CPRD_CPRD_Pos 0
05388 #define PWM_CPRD_CPRD_Msk (0xffffffffu << PWM_CPRD_CPRD_Pos) /**< \brief (PWM_CPRD) Channel Period */
05389 #define PWM_CPRD_CPRD(value) ((PWM_CPRD_CPRD_Msk & ((value) << PWM_CPRD_CPRD_Pos)))
05390 /* -------- PWM_CCNT : (PWM Offset: N/A) PWM Channel Counter Register -------- */
05391 #define PWM_CCNT_CNT_Pos 0
05392 #define PWM_CCNT_CNT_Msk (0xffffffffu << PWM_CCNT_CNT_Pos) /**< \brief (PWM_CCNT) Channel Counter Register */
05393 /* -------- PWM_CUPD : (PWM Offset: N/A) PWM Channel Update Register -------- */
05394 #define PWM_CUPD_CUPD_Pos 0
05395 #define PWM_CUPD_CUPD_Msk (0xffffffffu << PWM_CUPD_CUPD_Pos) /**< \brief (PWM_CUPD)  */
05396 #define PWM_CUPD_CUPD(value) ((PWM_CUPD_CUPD_Msk & ((value) << PWM_CUPD_CUPD_Pos)))
05397 
05398 /*@}*/

05403 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_RSTC Reset Controller */
05404 /*@{*/
05405 
05406 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
05407 /** \brief Rstc hardware registers */
05408 typedef struct {
05409   WoReg RSTC_CR; /**< \brief (Rstc Offset: 0x00) Control Register */
05410   RoReg RSTC_SR; /**< \brief (Rstc Offset: 0x04) Status Register */
05411   RwReg RSTC_MR; /**< \brief (Rstc Offset: 0x08) Mode Register */
05412 } Rstc;
05413 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
05414 /* -------- RSTC_CR : (RSTC Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
05415 #define RSTC_CR_PROCRST (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RSTC_CR) Processor Reset */
05416 #define RSTC_CR_PERRST (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RSTC_CR) Peripheral Reset */
05417 #define RSTC_CR_EXTRST (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RSTC_CR) External Reset */
05418 #define RSTC_CR_KEY_Pos 24
05419 #define RSTC_CR_KEY_Msk (0xffu << RSTC_CR_KEY_Pos) /**< \brief (RSTC_CR) Password */
05420 #define RSTC_CR_KEY(value) ((RSTC_CR_KEY_Msk & ((value) << RSTC_CR_KEY_Pos)))
05421 /* -------- RSTC_SR : (RSTC Offset: 0x04) Status Register -------- */

05423 #define RSTC_SR_RSTTYP_Pos 8
05424 #define RSTC_SR_RSTTYP_Msk (0x7u << RSTC_SR_RSTTYP_Pos) /**< \brief (RSTC_SR) Reset Type */
05425 #define RSTC_SR_NRSTL (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (RSTC_SR) NRST Pin Level */
05426 #define RSTC_SR_SRCMP (0x1u << 17) /**< \brief (RSTC_SR) Software Reset Command in Progress */
05427 /* -------- RSTC_MR : (RSTC Offset: 0x08) Mode Register -------- */
05428 #define RSTC_MR_ERSTL_Pos 8
05429 #define RSTC_MR_ERSTL_Msk (0xfu << RSTC_MR_ERSTL_Pos) /**< \brief (RSTC_MR) External Reset Length */
05430 #define RSTC_MR_ERSTL(value) ((RSTC_MR_ERSTL_Msk & ((value) << RSTC_MR_ERSTL_Pos)))
05431 #define RSTC_MR_KEY_Pos 24
05432 #define RSTC_MR_KEY_Msk (0xffu << RSTC_MR_KEY_Pos) /**< \brief (RSTC_MR) Password */
05433 #define RSTC_MR_KEY(value) ((RSTC_MR_KEY_Msk & ((value) << RSTC_MR_KEY_Pos)))
05434 
05435 /*@}*/

05437 /* ============================================================================= */
05438 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Real-time Clock */
05439 /* ============================================================================= */
05440 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_RTC Real-time Clock */
05441 /*@{*/
05442 
05443 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
05444 /** \brief Rtc hardware registers */
05445 typedef struct {
05446   RwReg RTC_CR;     /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x00) Control Register */
05447   RwReg RTC_MR;     /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x04) Mode Register */
05448   RwReg RTC_TIMR;   /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x08) Time Register */
05449   RwReg RTC_CALR;   /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x0C) Calendar Register */
05450   RwReg RTC_TIMALR; /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x10) Time Alarm Register */
05451   RwReg RTC_CALALR; /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x14) Calendar Alarm Register */
05452   RoReg RTC_SR;     /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x18) Status Register */
05453   WoReg RTC_SCCR;   /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x1C) Status Clear Command Register */
05454   WoReg RTC_IER;    /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x20) Interrupt Enable Register */
05455   WoReg RTC_IDR;    /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x24) Interrupt Disable Register */
05456   RoReg RTC_IMR;    /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x28) Interrupt Mask Register */
05457   RoReg RTC_VER;    /**< \brief (Rtc Offset: 0x2C) Valid Entry Register */
05458 } Rtc;
05459 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
05460 /* -------- RTC_CR : (RTC Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
05461 #define RTC_CR_UPDTIM (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Update Request Time Register */
05462 #define RTC_CR_UPDCAL (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Update Request Calendar Register */
05463 #define RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_Pos 8
05464 #define RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_Msk (0x3u << RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Time Event Selection */
05465 #define   RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_MINUTE (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Minute change */
05466 #define   RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_HOUR (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Hour change */
05467 #define   RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_MIDNIGHT (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Every day at midnight */
05468 #define   RTC_CR_TIMEVSEL_NOON (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Every day at noon */
05469 #define RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_Pos 16
05470 #define RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_Msk (0x3u << RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Calendar Event Selection */
05471 #define   RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_WEEK (0x0u << 16) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Week change (every Monday at time 00:00:00) */
05472 #define   RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_MONTH (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Month change (every 01 of each month at time 00:00:00) */
05473 #define   RTC_CR_CALEVSEL_YEAR (0x2u << 16) /**< \brief (RTC_CR) Year change (every January 1 at time 00:00:00) */
05474 /* -------- RTC_MR : (RTC Offset: 0x04) Mode Register -------- */
05475 #define RTC_MR_HRMOD (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_MR) 12-/24-hour Mode */
05476 /* -------- RTC_TIMR : (RTC Offset: 0x08) Time Register -------- */
05477 #define RTC_TIMR_SEC_Pos 0
05478 #define RTC_TIMR_SEC_Msk (0x7fu << RTC_TIMR_SEC_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMR) Current Second */
05479 #define RTC_TIMR_SEC(value) ((RTC_TIMR_SEC_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMR_SEC_Pos)))
05480 #define RTC_TIMR_MIN_Pos 8
05481 #define RTC_TIMR_MIN_Msk (0x7fu << RTC_TIMR_MIN_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMR) Current Minute */
05482 #define RTC_TIMR_MIN(value) ((RTC_TIMR_MIN_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMR_MIN_Pos)))
05483 #define RTC_TIMR_HOUR_Pos 16
05484 #define RTC_TIMR_HOUR_Msk (0x3fu << RTC_TIMR_HOUR_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMR) Current Hour */
05485 #define RTC_TIMR_HOUR(value) ((RTC_TIMR_HOUR_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMR_HOUR_Pos)))
05486 #define RTC_TIMR_AMPM (0x1u << 22) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMR) Ante Meridiem Post Meridiem Indicator */
05487 /* -------- RTC_CALR : (RTC Offset: 0x0C) Calendar Register -------- */
05488 #define RTC_CALR_CENT_Pos 0
05489 #define RTC_CALR_CENT_Msk (0x7fu << RTC_CALR_CENT_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALR) Current Century */
05490 #define RTC_CALR_CENT(value) ((RTC_CALR_CENT_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALR_CENT_Pos)))
05491 #define RTC_CALR_YEAR_Pos 8
05492 #define RTC_CALR_YEAR_Msk (0xffu << RTC_CALR_YEAR_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALR) Current Year */
05493 #define RTC_CALR_YEAR(value) ((RTC_CALR_YEAR_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALR_YEAR_Pos)))
05494 #define RTC_CALR_MONTH_Pos 16
05495 #define RTC_CALR_MONTH_Msk (0x1fu << RTC_CALR_MONTH_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALR) Current Month */
05496 #define RTC_CALR_MONTH(value) ((RTC_CALR_MONTH_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALR_MONTH_Pos)))
05497 #define RTC_CALR_DAY_Pos 21
05498 #define RTC_CALR_DAY_Msk (0x7u << RTC_CALR_DAY_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALR) Current Day in Current Week */
05499 #define RTC_CALR_DAY(value) ((RTC_CALR_DAY_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALR_DAY_Pos)))
05500 #define RTC_CALR_DATE_Pos 24
05501 #define RTC_CALR_DATE_Msk (0x3fu << RTC_CALR_DATE_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALR) Current Day in Current Month */
05502 #define RTC_CALR_DATE(value) ((RTC_CALR_DATE_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALR_DATE_Pos)))
05503 /* -------- RTC_TIMALR : (RTC Offset: 0x10) Time Alarm Register -------- */
05504 #define RTC_TIMALR_SEC_Pos 0
05505 #define RTC_TIMALR_SEC_Msk (0x7fu << RTC_TIMALR_SEC_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Second Alarm */
05506 #define RTC_TIMALR_SEC(value) ((RTC_TIMALR_SEC_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMALR_SEC_Pos)))
05507 #define RTC_TIMALR_SECEN (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Second Alarm Enable */
05508 #define RTC_TIMALR_MIN_Pos 8
05509 #define RTC_TIMALR_MIN_Msk (0x7fu << RTC_TIMALR_MIN_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Minute Alarm */
05510 #define RTC_TIMALR_MIN(value) ((RTC_TIMALR_MIN_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMALR_MIN_Pos)))
05511 #define RTC_TIMALR_MINEN (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Minute Alarm Enable */
05512 #define RTC_TIMALR_HOUR_Pos 16
05513 #define RTC_TIMALR_HOUR_Msk (0x3fu << RTC_TIMALR_HOUR_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Hour Alarm */
05514 #define RTC_TIMALR_HOUR(value) ((RTC_TIMALR_HOUR_Msk & ((value) << RTC_TIMALR_HOUR_Pos)))
05515 #define RTC_TIMALR_AMPM (0x1u << 22) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) AM/PM Indicator */
05516 #define RTC_TIMALR_HOUREN (0x1u << 23) /**< \brief (RTC_TIMALR) Hour Alarm Enable */
05517 /* -------- RTC_CALALR : (RTC Offset: 0x14) Calendar Alarm Register -------- */
05518 #define RTC_CALALR_MONTH_Pos 16
05519 #define RTC_CALALR_MONTH_Msk (0x1fu << RTC_CALALR_MONTH_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALALR) Month Alarm */
05520 #define RTC_CALALR_MONTH(value) ((RTC_CALALR_MONTH_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALALR_MONTH_Pos)))
05521 #define RTC_CALALR_MTHEN (0x1u << 23) /**< \brief (RTC_CALALR) Month Alarm Enable */
05522 #define RTC_CALALR_DATE_Pos 24
05523 #define RTC_CALALR_DATE_Msk (0x3fu << RTC_CALALR_DATE_Pos) /**< \brief (RTC_CALALR) Date Alarm */
05524 #define RTC_CALALR_DATE(value) ((RTC_CALALR_DATE_Msk & ((value) << RTC_CALALR_DATE_Pos)))
05525 #define RTC_CALALR_DATEEN (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (RTC_CALALR) Date Alarm Enable */
05526 /* -------- RTC_SR : (RTC Offset: 0x18) Status Register -------- */
05527 #define RTC_SR_ACKUPD (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_SR) Acknowledge for Update */
05528 #define RTC_SR_ALARM (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_SR) Alarm Flag */
05529 #define RTC_SR_SEC (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_SR) Second Event */
05530 #define RTC_SR_TIMEV (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_SR) Time Event */
05531 #define RTC_SR_CALEV (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (RTC_SR) Calendar Event */
05532 /* -------- RTC_SCCR : (RTC Offset: 0x1C) Status Clear Command Register -------- */
05533 #define RTC_SCCR_ACKCLR (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_SCCR) Acknowledge Clear */
05534 #define RTC_SCCR_ALRCLR (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_SCCR) Alarm Clear */
05535 #define RTC_SCCR_SECCLR (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_SCCR) Second Clear */
05536 #define RTC_SCCR_TIMCLR (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_SCCR) Time Clear */
05537 #define RTC_SCCR_CALCLR (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (RTC_SCCR) Calendar Clear */
05538 /* -------- RTC_IER : (RTC Offset: 0x20) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
05539 #define RTC_IER_ACKEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_IER) Acknowledge Update Interrupt Enable */
05540 #define RTC_IER_ALREN (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_IER) Alarm Interrupt Enable */
05541 #define RTC_IER_SECEN (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_IER) Second Event Interrupt Enable */
05542 #define RTC_IER_TIMEN (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_IER) Time Event Interrupt Enable */
05543 #define RTC_IER_CALEN (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (RTC_IER) Calendar Event Interrupt Enable */
05544 /* -------- RTC_IDR : (RTC Offset: 0x24) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
05545 #define RTC_IDR_ACKDIS (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_IDR) Acknowledge Update Interrupt Disable */
05546 #define RTC_IDR_ALRDIS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_IDR) Alarm Interrupt Disable */
05547 #define RTC_IDR_SECDIS (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_IDR) Second Event Interrupt Disable */
05548 #define RTC_IDR_TIMDIS (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_IDR) Time Event Interrupt Disable */
05549 #define RTC_IDR_CALDIS (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (RTC_IDR) Calendar Event Interrupt Disable */
05550 /* -------- RTC_IMR : (RTC Offset: 0x28) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
05551 #define RTC_IMR_ACK (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_IMR) Acknowledge Update Interrupt Mask */
05552 #define RTC_IMR_ALR (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_IMR) Alarm Interrupt Mask */
05553 #define RTC_IMR_SEC (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_IMR) Second Event Interrupt Mask */
05554 #define RTC_IMR_TIM (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_IMR) Time Event Interrupt Mask */
05555 #define RTC_IMR_CAL (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (RTC_IMR) Calendar Event Interrupt Mask */
05556 /* -------- RTC_VER : (RTC Offset: 0x2C) Valid Entry Register -------- */
05557 #define RTC_VER_NVTIM (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (RTC_VER) Non-valid Time */
05558 #define RTC_VER_NVCAL (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (RTC_VER) Non-valid Calendar */
05559 #define RTC_VER_NVTIMALR (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (RTC_VER) Non-valid Time Alarm */
05560 #define RTC_VER_NVCALALR (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (RTC_VER) Non-valid Calendar Alarm */
05561 
05562 /*@}*/

05627 } Smc;

05633 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP_Pos 8
05634 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP_Msk (0x3fu << SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_SETUP) NCS Setup Length in WRITE Access */
05635 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP(value) ((SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP_Msk & ((value) << SMC_SETUP_NCS_WR_SETUP_Pos)))
05636 #define SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP_Pos 16
05637 #define SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP_Msk (0x3fu << SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_SETUP) NRD Setup Length */
05638 #define SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP(value) ((SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP_Msk & ((value) << SMC_SETUP_NRD_SETUP_Pos)))
05639 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP_Pos 24
05640 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP_Msk (0x3fu << SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_SETUP) NCS Setup Length in READ Access */
05641 #define SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP(value) ((SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP_Msk & ((value) << SMC_SETUP_NCS_RD_SETUP_Pos)))
05642 /* -------- SMC_PULSE : (SMC Offset: N/A) SMC Pulse Register -------- */
05643 #define SMC_PULSE_NWE_PULSE_Pos 0

05646 #define SMC_PULSE_NCS_WR_PULSE_Pos 8

05648 #define SMC_PULSE_NCS_WR_PULSE(value) ((SMC_PULSE_NCS_WR_PULSE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_PULSE_NCS_WR_PULSE_Pos)))
05649 #define SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE_Pos 16
05650 #define SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE_Msk (0x7fu << SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_PULSE) NRD Pulse Length */
05651 #define SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE(value) ((SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_PULSE_NRD_PULSE_Pos)))
05652 #define SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE_Pos 24
05653 #define SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE_Msk (0x7fu << SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_PULSE) NCS Pulse Length in READ Access */
05654 #define SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE(value) ((SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_PULSE_NCS_RD_PULSE_Pos)))
05655 /* -------- SMC_CYCLE : (SMC Offset: N/A) SMC Cycle Register -------- */
05656 #define SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE_Pos 0
05657 #define SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE_Msk (0x1ffu << SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_CYCLE) Total Write Cycle Length */
05658 #define SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE(value) ((SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_CYCLE_NWE_CYCLE_Pos)))
05659 #define SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE_Pos 16
05660 #define SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE_Msk (0x1ffu << SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_CYCLE) Total Read Cycle Length */
05661 #define SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE(value) ((SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_CYCLE_NRD_CYCLE_Pos)))
05662 /* -------- SMC_MODE : (SMC Offset: N/A) SMC Mode Register -------- */
05663 #define SMC_MODE_READ_MODE (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE)  */
05664 #define SMC_MODE_WRITE_MODE (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE)  */
05665 #define SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE_Pos 4
05666 #define SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE_Msk (0x3u << SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) NWAIT Mode */
05667 #define SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE(value) ((SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE_Msk & ((value) << SMC_MODE_EXNW_MODE_Pos)))
05668 #define SMC_MODE_BAT (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) Byte Access Type */
05669 #define SMC_MODE_DBW_Pos 12
05670 #define SMC_MODE_DBW_Msk (0x3u << SMC_MODE_DBW_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) Data Bus Width */
05671 #define SMC_MODE_DBW(value) ((SMC_MODE_DBW_Msk & ((value) << SMC_MODE_DBW_Pos)))
05672 #define SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES_Pos 16
05673 #define SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES_Msk (0xfu << SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) Data Float Time */
05674 #define SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES(value) ((SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES_Msk & ((value) << SMC_MODE_TDF_CYCLES_Pos)))
05675 #define SMC_MODE_TDF_MODE (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) TDF Optimization */
05676 #define SMC_MODE_PMEN (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) Page Mode Enabled */
05677 #define SMC_MODE_PS_Pos 28
05678 #define SMC_MODE_PS_Msk (0x3u << SMC_MODE_PS_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_MODE) Page Size */
05679 #define SMC_MODE_PS(value) ((SMC_MODE_PS_Msk & ((value) << SMC_MODE_PS_Pos)))
05680 /* -------- SMC_DELAY1 : (SMC Offset: 0xC0) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05681 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay1_Pos 0
05682 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay1_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay1_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05683 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay1(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay1_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay1_Pos)))
05684 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay2_Pos 4
05685 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay2_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay2_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05686 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay2(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay2_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay2_Pos)))
05687 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay3_Pos 8
05688 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay3_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay3_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05689 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay3(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay3_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay3_Pos)))
05690 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay4_Pos 12
05691 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay4_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay4_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05692 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay4(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay4_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay4_Pos)))
05693 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay5_Pos 16
05694 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay5_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay5_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05695 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay5(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay5_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay5_Pos)))
05696 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay6_Pos 20
05697 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay6_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay6_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05698 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay6(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay6_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay6_Pos)))
05699 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay7_Pos 24
05700 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay7_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay7_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05701 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay7(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay7_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay7_Pos)))
05702 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay8_Pos 28
05703 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay8_Msk (0xfu << SMC_DELAY1_Delay8_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_DELAY1)  */
05704 #define SMC_DELAY1_Delay8(value) ((SMC_DELAY1_Delay8_Msk & ((value) << SMC_DELAY1_Delay8_Pos)))
05705 /* -------- SMC_DELAY2 : (SMC Offset: 0xC4) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05706 /* -------- SMC_DELAY3 : (SMC Offset: 0xC8) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05707 /* -------- SMC_DELAY4 : (SMC Offset: 0xCC) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05708 /* -------- SMC_DELAY5 : (SMC Offset: 0xD0) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05709 /* -------- SMC_DELAY6 : (SMC Offset: 0xD4) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05710 /* -------- SMC_DELAY7 : (SMC Offset: 0xD8) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05711 /* -------- SMC_DELAY8 : (SMC Offset: 0xDC) SMC Delay on I/O -------- */
05712 /* -------- SMC_WPMR : (SMC Offset: 0xE4) SMC Write Protect Mode Register -------- */
05713 #define SMC_WPMR_WPEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SMC_WPMR) Write Protect Enable */
05714 #define SMC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos 8
05715 #define SMC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk (0xffffffu << SMC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_WPMR) Write Protect KEY */
05716 #define SMC_WPMR_WPKEY(value) ((SMC_WPMR_WPKEY_Msk & ((value) << SMC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos)))
05717 /* -------- SMC_WPSR : (SMC Offset: 0xE8) SMC Write Protect Status Register -------- */
05718 #define SMC_WPSR_WPVS (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SMC_WPSR) Write Protect Enable */
05719 #define SMC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos 8
05720 #define SMC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Msk (0xffffu << SMC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos) /**< \brief (SMC_WPSR) Write Protect Violation Source */
05721
