05729 
05730 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
05731 /** \brief Spi hardware registers */
05732 typedef struct {
05733   WoReg SPI_CR;        /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x00) Control Register */
05734   RwReg SPI_MR;        /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x04) Mode Register */
05735   RoReg SPI_RDR;       /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x08) Receive Data Register */
05736   WoReg SPI_TDR;       /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x0C) Transmit Data Register */
05737   RoReg SPI_SR;        /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x10) Status Register */
05738   WoReg SPI_IER;       /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x14) Interrupt Enable Register */
05739   WoReg SPI_IDR;       /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x18) Interrupt Disable Register */
05740   RoReg SPI_IMR;       /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x1C) Interrupt Mask Register */
05741   RoReg Reserved1[4];
05742   RwReg SPI_CSR[4];    /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0x30) Chip Select Register */
05743   RoReg Reserved2[41];
05744   RwReg SPI_WPMR;      /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0xE4) Write Protection Control Register */
05745   RoReg SPI_WPSR;      /**< \brief (Spi Offset: 0xE8) Write Protection Status Register */
05746 } Spi;
05747 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
05748 /* -------- SPI_CR : (SPI Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
05749 #define SPI_CR_SPIEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_CR) SPI Enable */
05750 #define SPI_CR_SPIDIS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_CR) SPI Disable */
05751 #define SPI_CR_SWRST (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (SPI_CR) SPI Software Reset */
05752 #define SPI_CR_LASTXFER (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (SPI_CR) Last Transfer */
05753 /* -------- SPI_MR : (SPI Offset: 0x04) Mode Register -------- */
05754 #define SPI_MR_MSTR (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Master/Slave Mode */
05755 #define SPI_MR_PS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Peripheral Select */
05756 #define SPI_MR_PCSDEC (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Chip Select Decode */
05757 #define SPI_MR_MODFDIS (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Mode Fault Detection */
05758 #define SPI_MR_WDRBT (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Wait Data Read Before Transfer */
05759 #define SPI_MR_LLB (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Local Loopback Enable */
05760 #define SPI_MR_PCS_Pos 16
05761 #define SPI_MR_PCS_Msk (0xfu << SPI_MR_PCS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Peripheral Chip Select */
05762 #define SPI_MR_PCS(value) ((SPI_MR_PCS_Msk & ((value) << SPI_MR_PCS_Pos)))
05763 #define SPI_MR_DLYBCS_Pos 24
05764 #define SPI_MR_DLYBCS_Msk (0xffu << SPI_MR_DLYBCS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_MR) Delay Between Chip Selects */
05765 #define SPI_MR_DLYBCS(value) ((SPI_MR_DLYBCS_Msk & ((value) << SPI_MR_DLYBCS_Pos)))
05766 /* -------- SPI_RDR : (SPI Offset: 0x08) Receive Data Register -------- */
05767 #define SPI_RDR_RD_Pos 0
05768 #define SPI_RDR_RD_Msk (0xffffu << SPI_RDR_RD_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_RDR) Receive Data */
05769 #define SPI_RDR_PCS_Pos 16
05770 #define SPI_RDR_PCS_Msk (0xfu << SPI_RDR_PCS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_RDR) Peripheral Chip Select */
05771 /* -------- SPI_TDR : (SPI Offset: 0x0C) Transmit Data Register -------- */
05772 #define SPI_TDR_TD_Pos 0
05773 #define SPI_TDR_TD_Msk (0xffffu << SPI_TDR_TD_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_TDR) Transmit Data */
05774 #define SPI_TDR_TD(value) ((SPI_TDR_TD_Msk & ((value) << SPI_TDR_TD_Pos)))
05775 #define SPI_TDR_PCS_Pos 16
05776 #define SPI_TDR_PCS_Msk (0xfu << SPI_TDR_PCS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_TDR) Peripheral Chip Select */
05777 #define SPI_TDR_PCS(value) ((SPI_TDR_PCS_Msk & ((value) << SPI_TDR_PCS_Pos)))
05778 #define SPI_TDR_LASTXFER (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (SPI_TDR) Last Transfer */
05779 /* -------- SPI_SR : (SPI Offset: 0x10) Status Register -------- */
05780 #define SPI_SR_RDRF (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) Receive Data Register Full */
05781 #define SPI_SR_TDRE (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) Transmit Data Register Empty */
05782 #define SPI_SR_MODF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) Mode Fault Error */
05783 #define SPI_SR_OVRES (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) Overrun Error Status */
05784 #define SPI_SR_NSSR (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) NSS Rising */
05785 #define SPI_SR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) Transmission Registers Empty */
05786 #define SPI_SR_SPIENS (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (SPI_SR) SPI Enable Status */
05787 /* -------- SPI_IER : (SPI Offset: 0x14) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
05788 #define SPI_IER_RDRF (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) Receive Data Register Full Interrupt Enable */
05789 #define SPI_IER_TDRE (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) SPI Transmit Data Register Empty Interrupt Enable */
05790 #define SPI_IER_MODF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) Mode Fault Error Interrupt Enable */
05791 #define SPI_IER_OVRES (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) Overrun Error Interrupt Enable */
05792 #define SPI_IER_NSSR (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) NSS Rising Interrupt Enable */
05793 #define SPI_IER_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SPI_IER) Transmission Registers Empty Enable */
05794 /* -------- SPI_IDR : (SPI Offset: 0x18) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
05795 #define SPI_IDR_RDRF (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) Receive Data Register Full Interrupt Disable */
05796 #define SPI_IDR_TDRE (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) SPI Transmit Data Register Empty Interrupt Disable */
05797 #define SPI_IDR_MODF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) Mode Fault Error Interrupt Disable */
05798 #define SPI_IDR_OVRES (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) Overrun Error Interrupt Disable */
05799 #define SPI_IDR_NSSR (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) NSS Rising Interrupt Disable */
05800 #define SPI_IDR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SPI_IDR) Transmission Registers Empty Disable */
05801 /* -------- SPI_IMR : (SPI Offset: 0x1C) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
05802 #define SPI_IMR_RDRF (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) Receive Data Register Full Interrupt Mask */
05803 #define SPI_IMR_TDRE (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) SPI Transmit Data Register Empty Interrupt Mask */
05804 #define SPI_IMR_MODF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) Mode Fault Error Interrupt Mask */
05805 #define SPI_IMR_OVRES (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) Overrun Error Interrupt Mask */
05806 #define SPI_IMR_NSSR (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) NSS Rising Interrupt Mask */
05807 #define SPI_IMR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SPI_IMR) Transmission Registers Empty Mask */
05808 /* -------- SPI_CSR[4] : (SPI Offset: 0x30) Chip Select Register -------- */
05809 #define SPI_CSR_CPOL (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Clock Polarity */
05810 #define SPI_CSR_NCPHA (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Clock Phase */
05811 #define SPI_CSR_CSAAT (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Chip Select Active After Transfer */
05812 #define SPI_CSR_BITS_Pos 4
05813 #define SPI_CSR_BITS_Msk (0xfu << SPI_CSR_BITS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Bits Per Transfer */
05814 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_8_BIT (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 8 bits for transfer */
05815 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_9_BIT (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 9 bits for transfer */
05816 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_10_BIT (0x2u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 10 bits for transfer */
05817 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_11_BIT (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 11 bits for transfer */
05818 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_12_BIT (0x4u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 12 bits for transfer */
05819 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_13_BIT (0x5u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 13 bits for transfer */
05820 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_14_BIT (0x6u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 14 bits for transfer */
05821 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_15_BIT (0x7u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 15 bits for transfer */
05822 #define   SPI_CSR_BITS_16_BIT (0x8u << 4) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) 16 bits for transfer */
05823 #define SPI_CSR_SCBR_Pos 8
05824 #define SPI_CSR_SCBR_Msk (0xffu << SPI_CSR_SCBR_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Serial Clock Baud Rate */
05825 #define SPI_CSR_SCBR(value) ((SPI_CSR_SCBR_Msk & ((value) << SPI_CSR_SCBR_Pos)))
05826 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBS_Pos 16
05827 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBS_Msk (0xffu << SPI_CSR_DLYBS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Delay Before SPCK */
05828 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBS(value) ((SPI_CSR_DLYBS_Msk & ((value) << SPI_CSR_DLYBS_Pos)))
05829 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBCT_Pos 24
05830 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBCT_Msk (0xffu << SPI_CSR_DLYBCT_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_CSR[4]) Delay Between Consecutive Transfers */
05831 #define SPI_CSR_DLYBCT(value) ((SPI_CSR_DLYBCT_Msk & ((value) << SPI_CSR_DLYBCT_Pos)))
05832 /* -------- SPI_WPMR : (SPI Offset: 0xE4) Write Protection Control Register -------- */
05833 #define SPI_WPMR_SPIWPEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SPI_WPMR) SPI Write Protection Enable */
05834 #define SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY_Pos 8
05835 #define SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY_Msk (0xffffffu << SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_WPMR) SPI Write Protection Key Password */
05836 #define SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY(value) ((SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY_Msk & ((value) << SPI_WPMR_SPIWPKEY_Pos)))
05837 /* -------- SPI_WPSR : (SPI Offset: 0xE8) Write Protection Status Register -------- */
05838 #define SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVS_Pos 0
05839 #define SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVS_Msk (0x7u << SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVS_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_WPSR) SPI Write Protection Violation Status */
05840 #define SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVSRC_Pos 8
05841 #define SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVSRC_Msk (0xffu << SPI_WPSR_SPIWPVSRC_Pos) /**< \brief (SPI_WPSR) SPI Write Protection Violation Source */
05842 
05843 /*@}*/

05845 /* ============================================================================= */
05846 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Synchronous Serial Controller */

05848 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_SSC Synchronous Serial Controller */

05850 
05851 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
05852 /** \brief Ssc hardware registers */
05853 typedef struct {
05854   WoReg SSC_CR;        /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x0) Control Register */
05855   RwReg SSC_CMR;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x4) Clock Mode Register */
05856   RoReg Reserved1[2];
05857   RwReg SSC_RCMR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x10) Receive Clock Mode Register */
05858   RwReg SSC_RFMR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x14) Receive Frame Mode Register */
05859   RwReg SSC_TCMR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x18) Transmit Clock Mode Register */
05860   RwReg SSC_TFMR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x1C) Transmit Frame Mode Register */
05861   RoReg SSC_RHR;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x20) Receive Holding Register */
05862   WoReg SSC_THR;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x24) Transmit Holding Register */
05863   RoReg Reserved2[2];
05864   RoReg SSC_RSHR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x30) Receive Sync. Holding Register */
05865   RwReg SSC_TSHR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x34) Transmit Sync. Holding Register */
05866   RwReg SSC_RC0R;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x38) Receive Compare 0 Register */
05867   RwReg SSC_RC1R;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x3C) Receive Compare 1 Register */
05868   RoReg SSC_SR;        /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x40) Status Register */
05869   WoReg SSC_IER;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x44) Interrupt Enable Register */
05870   WoReg SSC_IDR;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x48) Interrupt Disable Register */
05871   RoReg SSC_IMR;       /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0x4C) Interrupt Mask Register */
05872   RoReg Reserved3[37];
05873   RwReg SSC_WPMR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0xE4) Write Protect Mode Register */
05874   RoReg SSC_WPSR;      /**< \brief (Ssc Offset: 0xE8) Write Protect Status Register */
05875 } Ssc;
05876 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
05877 /* -------- SSC_CR : (SSC Offset: 0x0) Control Register -------- */
05878 #define SSC_CR_RXEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_CR) Receive Enable */
05879 #define SSC_CR_RXDIS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SSC_CR) Receive Disable */
05880 #define SSC_CR_TXEN (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_CR) Transmit Enable */
05881 #define SSC_CR_TXDIS (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SSC_CR) Transmit Disable */
05882 #define SSC_CR_SWRST (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (SSC_CR) Software Reset */
05883 /* -------- SSC_CMR : (SSC Offset: 0x4) Clock Mode Register -------- */
05884 #define SSC_CMR_DIV_Pos 0
05885 #define SSC_CMR_DIV_Msk (0xfffu << SSC_CMR_DIV_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_CMR) Clock Divider */
05886 #define SSC_CMR_DIV(value) ((SSC_CMR_DIV_Msk & ((value) << SSC_CMR_DIV_Pos)))
05887 /* -------- SSC_RCMR : (SSC Offset: 0x10) Receive Clock Mode Register -------- */
05888 #define SSC_RCMR_CKS_Pos 0
05889 #define SSC_RCMR_CKS_Msk (0x3u << SSC_RCMR_CKS_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock Selection */
05890 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKS_MCK (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Divided Clock */
05891 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKS_TK (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) TK Clock signal */
05892 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKS_RK (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) RK pin */
05893 #define SSC_RCMR_CKO_Pos 2
05894 #define SSC_RCMR_CKO_Msk (0x7u << SSC_RCMR_CKO_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock Output Mode Selection */
05895 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKO_NONE (0x0u << 2) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) None */
05896 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKO_CONTINUOUS (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Continuous Receive Clock */
05897 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKO_TRANSFER (0x2u << 2) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock only during data transfers */
05898 #define SSC_RCMR_CKI (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock Inversion */
05899 #define SSC_RCMR_CKG_Pos 6
05900 #define SSC_RCMR_CKG_Msk (0x3u << SSC_RCMR_CKG_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock Gating Selection */
05901 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKG_NONE (0x0u << 6) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) None */
05902 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKG_CONTINUOUS (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Continuous Receive Clock */
05903 #define   SSC_RCMR_CKG_TRANSFER (0x2u << 6) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Clock only during data transfers */
05904 #define SSC_RCMR_START_Pos 8
05905 #define SSC_RCMR_START_Msk (0xfu << SSC_RCMR_START_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Start Selection */
05906 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_CONTINUOUS (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Continuous, as soon as the receiver is enabled, and immediately after the end of transfer of the previous data. */
05907 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_TRANSMIT (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Transmit start */
05908 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_LOW (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of a low level on RF signal */
05909 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_HIGH (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of a high level on RF signal */
05910 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_FALLING (0x4u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of a falling edge on RF signal */
05911 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_RISING (0x5u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of a rising edge on RF signal */
05912 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_LEVEL (0x6u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of any level change on RF signal */
05913 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_RF_EDGE (0x7u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Detection of any edge on RF signal */
05914 #define   SSC_RCMR_START_CMP_0 (0x8u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Compare 0 */
05915 #define SSC_RCMR_STOP (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Stop Selection */
05916 #define SSC_RCMR_STTDLY_Pos 16
05917 #define SSC_RCMR_STTDLY_Msk (0xffu << SSC_RCMR_STTDLY_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Start Delay */
05918 #define SSC_RCMR_STTDLY(value) ((SSC_RCMR_STTDLY_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RCMR_STTDLY_Pos)))
05919 #define SSC_RCMR_PERIOD_Pos 24
05920 #define SSC_RCMR_PERIOD_Msk (0xffu << SSC_RCMR_PERIOD_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RCMR) Receive Period Divider Selection */
05921 #define SSC_RCMR_PERIOD(value) ((SSC_RCMR_PERIOD_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RCMR_PERIOD_Pos)))
05922 /* -------- SSC_RFMR : (SSC Offset: 0x14) Receive Frame Mode Register -------- */
05923 #define SSC_RFMR_DATLEN_Pos 0
05924 #define SSC_RFMR_DATLEN_Msk (0x1fu << SSC_RFMR_DATLEN_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Data Length */
05925 #define SSC_RFMR_DATLEN(value) ((SSC_RFMR_DATLEN_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RFMR_DATLEN_Pos)))
05926 #define SSC_RFMR_LOOP (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Loop Mode */
05927 #define SSC_RFMR_MSBF (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Most Significant Bit First */
05928 #define SSC_RFMR_DATNB_Pos 8
05929 #define SSC_RFMR_DATNB_Msk (0xfu << SSC_RFMR_DATNB_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Data Number per Frame */
05930 #define SSC_RFMR_DATNB(value) ((SSC_RFMR_DATNB_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RFMR_DATNB_Pos)))
05931 #define SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_Pos 16

05933 #define SSC_RFMR_FSLEN(value) ((SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_Pos)))
05934 #define SSC_RFMR_FSOS_Pos 20
05935 #define SSC_RFMR_FSOS_Msk (0x7u << SSC_RFMR_FSOS_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Receive Frame Sync Output Selection */
05936 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_NONE (0x0u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) None */
05937 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_NEGATIVE (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Negative Pulse */
05938 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_POSITIVE (0x2u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Positive Pulse */
05939 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_LOW (0x3u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Driven Low during data transfer */
05940 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_HIGH (0x4u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Driven High during data transfer */
05941 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSOS_TOGGLING (0x5u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Toggling at each start of data transfer */
05942 #define SSC_RFMR_FSEDGE (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Frame Sync Edge Detection */
05943 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSEDGE_POSITIVE (0x0u << 24) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Positive Edge Detection */
05944 #define   SSC_RFMR_FSEDGE_NEGATIVE (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) Negative Edge Detection */
05945 #define SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT_Pos 28
05946 #define SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT_Msk (0xfu << SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_RFMR) FSLEN Field Extension */
05947 #define SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT(value) ((SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT_Msk & ((value) << SSC_RFMR_FSLEN_EXT_Pos)))
05948 /* -------- SSC_TCMR : (SSC Offset: 0x18) Transmit Clock Mode Register -------- */
05949 #define SSC_TCMR_CKS_Pos 0
05950 #define SSC_TCMR_CKS_Msk (0x3u << SSC_TCMR_CKS_Pos) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Transmit Clock Selection */
05951 #define   SSC_TCMR_CKS_MCK (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Divided Clock */
05952 #define   SSC_TCMR_CKS_TK (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) TK Clock signal */

05954 #define SSC_TCMR_CKO_Pos 2

05960 #define SSC_TCMR_CKG_Pos 6

05965 #define SSC_TCMR_START_Pos 8

05967 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_CONTINUOUS (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Continuous, as soon as a word is written in the SSC_THR Register (if Transmit is enabled), and immediately after the end of transfer of the previous data. */
05968 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RECEIVE (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Receive start */
05969 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RF_LOW (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Detection of a low level on TF signal */

05971 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RF_FALLING (0x4u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Detection of a falling edge on TF signal */
05972 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RF_RISING (0x5u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Detection of a rising edge on TF signal */
05973 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RF_LEVEL (0x6u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Detection of any level change on TF signal */
05974 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_RF_EDGE (0x7u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Detection of any edge on TF signal */
05975 #define   SSC_TCMR_START_CMP_0 (0x8u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_TCMR) Compare 0 */
05976 #define SSC_TCMR_STTDLY_Pos 16

05979 #define SSC_TCMR_PERIOD_Pos 24

06000 #define   SSC_TFMR_FSOS_HIGH (0x4u << 20) /**< \brief (SSC_TFMR) Driven High during data transfer */

06031 /* -------- SSC_SR : (SSC Offset: 0x40) Status Register -------- */
06032 #define SSC_SR_TXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Transmit Ready */
06033 #define SSC_SR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Transmit Empty */
06034 #define SSC_SR_RXRDY (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Receive Ready */
06035 #define SSC_SR_OVRUN (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Receive Overrun */
06036 #define SSC_SR_CP0 (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Compare 0 */
06037 #define SSC_SR_CP1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Compare 1 */
06038 #define SSC_SR_TXSYN (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Transmit Sync */
06039 #define SSC_SR_RXSYN (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Receive Sync */
06040 #define SSC_SR_TXEN (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Transmit Enable */
06041 #define SSC_SR_RXEN (0x1u << 17) /**< \brief (SSC_SR) Receive Enable */
06042 /* -------- SSC_IER : (SSC Offset: 0x44) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
06043 #define SSC_IER_TXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Transmit Ready Interrupt Enable */
06044 #define SSC_IER_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Transmit Empty Interrupt Enable */
06045 #define SSC_IER_RXRDY (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Receive Ready Interrupt Enable */
06046 #define SSC_IER_OVRUN (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Receive Overrun Interrupt Enable */
06047 #define SSC_IER_CP0 (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Compare 0 Interrupt Enable */
06048 #define SSC_IER_CP1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Compare 1 Interrupt Enable */
06049 #define SSC_IER_TXSYN (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Tx Sync Interrupt Enable */
06050 #define SSC_IER_RXSYN (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (SSC_IER) Rx Sync Interrupt Enable */
06051 /* -------- SSC_IDR : (SSC Offset: 0x48) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
06052 #define SSC_IDR_TXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Transmit Ready Interrupt Disable */
06053 #define SSC_IDR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Transmit Empty Interrupt Disable */
06054 #define SSC_IDR_RXRDY (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Receive Ready Interrupt Disable */
06055 #define SSC_IDR_OVRUN (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Receive Overrun Interrupt Disable */
06056 #define SSC_IDR_CP0 (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Compare 0 Interrupt Disable */
06057 #define SSC_IDR_CP1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Compare 1 Interrupt Disable */

06059 #define SSC_IDR_RXSYN (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (SSC_IDR) Rx Sync Interrupt Enable */
06060 /* -------- SSC_IMR : (SSC Offset: 0x4C) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
06061 #define SSC_IMR_TXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_IMR) Transmit Ready Interrupt Mask */
06062 #define SSC_IMR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (SSC_IMR) Transmit Empty Interrupt Mask */

06068 #define SSC_IMR_RXSYN (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (SSC_IMR) Rx Sync Interrupt Mask */
06069 /* -------- SSC_WPMR : (SSC Offset: 0xE4) Write Protect Mode Register -------- */
06070 #define SSC_WPMR_WPEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (SSC_WPMR) Write Protect Enable */
06071 #define SSC_WPMR_WPKEY_Pos 8

06074 /* -------- SSC_WPSR : (SSC Offset: 0xE8) Write Protect Status Register -------- */

06076 #define SSC_WPSR_WPVSRC_Pos 8

06087 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
06088 /** \brief TcChannel hardware registers */
06089 typedef struct {
06090   RwReg      TC_CCR;        /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x0) Channel Control Register */
06091   RwReg      TC_CMR;        /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x4) Channel Mode Register */
06092   RoReg      Reserved1[2];
06093   RwReg      TC_CV;         /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x10) Counter Value */
06094   RwReg      TC_RA;         /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x14) Register A */
06095   RwReg      TC_RB;         /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x18) Register B */
06096   RwReg      TC_RC;         /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x1C) Register C */
06097   RwReg      TC_SR;         /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x20) Status Register */
06098   RwReg      TC_IER;        /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x24) Interrupt Enable Register */
06099   RwReg      TC_IDR;        /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x28) Interrupt Disable Register */
06100   RwReg      TC_IMR;        /**< \brief (TcChannel Offset: 0x2C) Interrupt Mask Register */
06101   RoReg      Reserved2[4];
06102 } TcChannel;
06103 /** \brief Tc hardware registers */
06104 #define TCCHANNEL_NUMBER 3
06105 typedef struct {
06106   TcChannel  TC_CHANNEL[TCCHANNEL_NUMBER]; /**< \brief (Tc Offset: 0x0) channel = 0 .. 2 */
06107   WoReg      TC_BCR;        /**< \brief (Tc Offset: 0xC0) Block Control Register */
06108   RwReg      TC_BMR;        /**< \brief (Tc Offset: 0xC4) Block Mode Register */
06109 } Tc;
06110 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
06111 /* -------- TC_CCR : (TC Offset: N/A) Channel Control Register -------- */
06112 #define TC_CCR_CLKEN (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CCR) Counter Clock Enable Command */
06113 #define TC_CCR_CLKDIS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TC_CCR) Counter Clock Disable Command */
06114 #define TC_CCR_SWTRG (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TC_CCR) Software Trigger Command */
06115 /* -------- TC_CMR : (TC Offset: N/A) Channel Mode Register -------- */
06116 #define TC_CMR_TCCLKS_Pos 0
06117 #define TC_CMR_TCCLKS_Msk (0x7u << TC_CMR_TCCLKS_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock Selection */
06118 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_TIMER_CLOCK1 (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: TCLK1 */
06119 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_TIMER_CLOCK2 (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: TCLK2 */
06120 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_TIMER_CLOCK3 (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: TCLK3 */
06121 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_TIMER_CLOCK4 (0x3u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: TCLK4 */
06122 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_TIMER_CLOCK5 (0x4u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: TCLK5 */
06123 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_XC0 (0x5u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: XC0 */
06124 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_XC1 (0x6u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: XC1 */
06125 #define   TC_CMR_TCCLKS_XC2 (0x7u << 0) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock selected: XC2 */
06126 #define TC_CMR_CLKI (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Clock Invert */
06127 #define TC_CMR_BURST_Pos 4
06128 #define TC_CMR_BURST_Msk (0x3u << TC_CMR_BURST_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Burst Signal Selection */
06129 #define   TC_CMR_BURST_NONE (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) The clock is not gated by an external signal. */
06130 #define   TC_CMR_BURST_XC0 (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) XC0 is ANDed with the selected clock. */
06131 #define   TC_CMR_BURST_XC1 (0x2u << 4) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) XC1 is ANDed with the selected clock. */
06132 #define   TC_CMR_BURST_XC2 (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) XC2 is ANDed with the selected clock. */
06133 #define TC_CMR_LDBSTOP (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Counter Clock Stopped with RB Loading */
06134 #define TC_CMR_LDBDIS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Counter Clock Disable with RB Loading */
06135 #define TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_Pos 8
06136 #define TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_Msk (0x3u << TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) External Trigger Edge Selection */
06137 #define   TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_NONE (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) The clock is not gated by an external signal. */
06138 #define   TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_RISING (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Rising edge */
06139 #define   TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_FALLING (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Falling edge */
06140 #define   TC_CMR_ETRGEDG_EDGE (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Each edge */
06141 #define TC_CMR_ABETRG (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) TIOA or TIOB External Trigger Selection */
06142 #define TC_CMR_CPCTRG (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) RC Compare Trigger Enable */
06143 #define TC_CMR_WAVE (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (TC_CMR)  */
06144 #define TC_CMR_LDRA_Pos 16
06145 #define TC_CMR_LDRA_Msk (0x3u << TC_CMR_LDRA_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) RA Loading Selection */
06146 #define   TC_CMR_LDRA_NONE (0x0u << 16) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) None */
06147 #define   TC_CMR_LDRA_RISING (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Rising edge of TIOA */
06148 #define   TC_CMR_LDRA_FALLING (0x2u << 16) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Falling edge of TIOA */
06149 #define   TC_CMR_LDRA_EDGE (0x3u << 16) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Each edge of TIOA */
06150 #define TC_CMR_LDRB_Pos 18
06151 #define TC_CMR_LDRB_Msk (0x3u << TC_CMR_LDRB_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) RB Loading Selection */
06152 #define   TC_CMR_LDRB_NONE (0x0u << 18) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) None */
06153 #define   TC_CMR_LDRB_RISING (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Rising edge of TIOA */
06154 #define   TC_CMR_LDRB_FALLING (0x2u << 18) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Falling edge of TIOA */
06155 #define   TC_CMR_LDRB_EDGE (0x3u << 18) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Each edge of TIOA */
06156 #define TC_CMR_CPCSTOP (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Counter Clock Stopped with RC Compare */
06157 #define TC_CMR_CPCDIS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Counter Clock Disable with RC Compare */
06158 #define TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_Pos 8
06159 #define TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_Msk (0x3u << TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_Pos) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) External Event Edge Selection */
06160 #define   TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_NONE (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) None */
06161 #define   TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_RISING (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Rising edge */
06162 #define   TC_CMR_EEVTEDG_FALLING (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) Falling edge */

06164 #define TC_CMR_EEVT_Pos 10

06166 #define   TC_CMR_EEVT_TIOB (0x0u << 10) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) TIOB */
06167 #define   TC_CMR_EEVT_XC0 (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) XC0 */
06168 #define   TC_CMR_EEVT_XC1 (0x2u << 10) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) XC1 */

06170 #define TC_CMR_ENETRG (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (TC_CMR) External Event Trigger Enable */
06171 #define TC_CMR_WAVSEL_Pos 13

06177 #define TC_CMR_ACPA_Pos 16

06251 #define TC_SR_MTIOB (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (TC_SR) TIOB Mirror */

06268 #define TC_IDR_LDRBS (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TC_IDR) RB Loading */
06269 #define TC_IDR_ETRGS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (TC_IDR) External Trigger */

06272 #define TC_IMR_LOVRS (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TC_IMR) Load Overrun */
06273 #define TC_IMR_CPAS (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TC_IMR) RA Compare */

06287 #define TC_BMR_TC1XC1S_Pos 2

06300 /* ============================================================================= */
06301 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Two-wire Interface */
06302 /* ============================================================================= */
06303 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_TWI Two-wire Interface */
06304 /*@{*/
06305 
06306 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
06307 /** \brief Twi hardware registers */
06308 typedef struct {
06309   WoReg TWI_CR;       /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x00) Control Register */
06310   RwReg TWI_MMR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x04) Master Mode Register */
06311   RwReg TWI_SMR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x08) Slave Mode Register */
06312   RwReg TWI_IADR;     /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x0C) Internal Address Register */
06313   RwReg TWI_CWGR;     /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x10) Clock Waveform Generator Register */
06314   RoReg Reserved1[3];
06315   RoReg TWI_SR;       /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x20) Status Register */
06316   WoReg TWI_IER;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x24) Interrupt Enable Register */
06317   WoReg TWI_IDR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x28) Interrupt Disable Register */
06318   RoReg TWI_IMR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x2C) Interrupt Mask Register */
06319   RoReg TWI_RHR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x30) Receive Holding Register */
06320   WoReg TWI_THR;      /**< \brief (Twi Offset: 0x34) Transmit Holding Register */
06321 } Twi;
06322 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
06323 /* -------- TWI_CR : (TWI Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
06324 #define TWI_CR_START (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) Send a START Condition */
06325 #define TWI_CR_STOP (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) Send a STOP Condition */
06326 #define TWI_CR_MSEN (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) TWI Master Mode Enabled */
06327 #define TWI_CR_MSDIS (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) TWI Master Mode Disabled */
06328 #define TWI_CR_SVEN (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) TWI Slave Mode Enabled */
06329 #define TWI_CR_SVDIS (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) TWI Slave Mode Disabled */
06330 #define TWI_CR_QUICK (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) SMBUS Quick Command */
06331 #define TWI_CR_SWRST (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (TWI_CR) Software Reset */
06332 /* -------- TWI_MMR : (TWI Offset: 0x04) Master Mode Register -------- */
06333 #define TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_Pos 8
06334 #define TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_Msk (0x3u << TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) Internal Device Address Size */
06335 #define   TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_NONE (0x0u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) No internal device address */
06336 #define   TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_1_BYTE (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) One-byte internal device address */
06337 #define   TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_2_BYTE (0x2u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) Two-byte internal device address */
06338 #define   TWI_MMR_IADRSZ_3_BYTE (0x3u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) Three-byte internal device address */
06339 #define TWI_MMR_MREAD (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) Master Read Direction */
06340 #define TWI_MMR_DADR_Pos 16
06341 #define TWI_MMR_DADR_Msk (0x7fu << TWI_MMR_DADR_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_MMR) Device Address */
06342 #define TWI_MMR_DADR(value) ((TWI_MMR_DADR_Msk & ((value) << TWI_MMR_DADR_Pos)))
06343 /* -------- TWI_SMR : (TWI Offset: 0x08) Slave Mode Register -------- */
06344 #define TWI_SMR_SADR_Pos 16
06345 #define TWI_SMR_SADR_Msk (0x7fu << TWI_SMR_SADR_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_SMR) Slave Address */
06346 #define TWI_SMR_SADR(value) ((TWI_SMR_SADR_Msk & ((value) << TWI_SMR_SADR_Pos)))
06347 /* -------- TWI_IADR : (TWI Offset: 0x0C) Internal Address Register -------- */
06348 #define TWI_IADR_IADR_Pos 0
06349 #define TWI_IADR_IADR_Msk (0xffffffu << TWI_IADR_IADR_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_IADR) Internal Address */
06350 #define TWI_IADR_IADR(value) ((TWI_IADR_IADR_Msk & ((value) << TWI_IADR_IADR_Pos)))
06351 /* -------- TWI_CWGR : (TWI Offset: 0x10) Clock Waveform Generator Register -------- */
06352 #define TWI_CWGR_CLDIV_Pos 0
06353 #define TWI_CWGR_CLDIV_Msk (0xffu << TWI_CWGR_CLDIV_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_CWGR) Clock Low Divider */
06354 #define TWI_CWGR_CLDIV(value) ((TWI_CWGR_CLDIV_Msk & ((value) << TWI_CWGR_CLDIV_Pos)))
06355 #define TWI_CWGR_CHDIV_Pos 8
06356 #define TWI_CWGR_CHDIV_Msk (0xffu << TWI_CWGR_CHDIV_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_CWGR) Clock High Divider */
06357 #define TWI_CWGR_CHDIV(value) ((TWI_CWGR_CHDIV_Msk & ((value) << TWI_CWGR_CHDIV_Pos)))
06358 #define TWI_CWGR_CKDIV_Pos 16
06359 #define TWI_CWGR_CKDIV_Msk (0x7u << TWI_CWGR_CKDIV_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_CWGR) Clock Divider */
06360 #define TWI_CWGR_CKDIV(value) ((TWI_CWGR_CKDIV_Msk & ((value) << TWI_CWGR_CKDIV_Pos)))
06361 /* -------- TWI_SR : (TWI Offset: 0x20) Status Register -------- */
06362 #define TWI_SR_TXCOMP (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Transmission Completed (automatically set / reset) */
06363 #define TWI_SR_RXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Receive Holding Register Ready (automatically set / reset) */
06364 #define TWI_SR_TXRDY (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Transmit Holding Register Ready (automatically set / reset) */
06365 #define TWI_SR_SVREAD (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Slave Read (automatically set / reset) */
06366 #define TWI_SR_SVACC (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Slave Access (automatically set / reset) */
06367 #define TWI_SR_GACC (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) General Call Access (clear on read) */
06368 #define TWI_SR_OVRE (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Overrun Error (clear on read) */
06369 #define TWI_SR_NACK (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Not Acknowledged (clear on read) */
06370 #define TWI_SR_ARBLST (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Arbitration Lost (clear on read) */
06371 #define TWI_SR_SCLWS (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) Clock Wait State (automatically set / reset) */
06372 #define TWI_SR_EOSACC (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (TWI_SR) End Of Slave Access (clear on read) */
06373 /* -------- TWI_IER : (TWI Offset: 0x24) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
06374 #define TWI_IER_TXCOMP (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Transmission Completed Interrupt Enable */
06375 #define TWI_IER_RXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Receive Holding Register Ready Interrupt Enable */
06376 #define TWI_IER_TXRDY (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Transmit Holding Register Ready Interrupt Enable */
06377 #define TWI_IER_SVACC (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Slave Access Interrupt Enable */
06378 #define TWI_IER_GACC (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) General Call Access Interrupt Enable */
06379 #define TWI_IER_OVRE (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Overrun Error Interrupt Enable */
06380 #define TWI_IER_NACK (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Not Acknowledge Interrupt Enable */
06381 #define TWI_IER_ARBLST (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Arbitration Lost Interrupt Enable */
06382 #define TWI_IER_SCL_WS (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) Clock Wait State Interrupt Enable */
06383 #define TWI_IER_EOSACC (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (TWI_IER) End Of Slave Access Interrupt Enable */
06384 /* -------- TWI_IDR : (TWI Offset: 0x28) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
06385 #define TWI_IDR_TXCOMP (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Transmission Completed Interrupt Disable */
06386 #define TWI_IDR_RXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Receive Holding Register Ready Interrupt Disable */
06387 #define TWI_IDR_TXRDY (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Transmit Holding Register Ready Interrupt Disable */
06388 #define TWI_IDR_SVACC (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Slave Access Interrupt Disable */
06389 #define TWI_IDR_GACC (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) General Call Access Interrupt Disable */
06390 #define TWI_IDR_OVRE (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Overrun Error Interrupt Disable */
06391 #define TWI_IDR_NACK (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Not Acknowledge Interrupt Disable */
06392 #define TWI_IDR_ARBLST (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Arbitration Lost Interrupt Disable */
06393 #define TWI_IDR_SCL_WS (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) Clock Wait State Interrupt Disable */
06394 #define TWI_IDR_EOSACC (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (TWI_IDR) End Of Slave Access Interrupt Disable */
06395 /* -------- TWI_IMR : (TWI Offset: 0x2C) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
06396 #define TWI_IMR_TXCOMP (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Transmission Completed Interrupt Mask */
06397 #define TWI_IMR_RXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Receive Holding Register Ready Interrupt Mask */
06398 #define TWI_IMR_TXRDY (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Transmit Holding Register Ready Interrupt Mask */
06399 #define TWI_IMR_SVACC (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Slave Access Interrupt Mask */
06400 #define TWI_IMR_GACC (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) General Call Access Interrupt Mask */
06401 #define TWI_IMR_OVRE (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Overrun Error Interrupt Mask */
06402 #define TWI_IMR_NACK (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Not Acknowledge Interrupt Mask */
06403 #define TWI_IMR_ARBLST (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Arbitration Lost Interrupt Mask */
06404 #define TWI_IMR_SCL_WS (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) Clock Wait State Interrupt Mask */
06405 #define TWI_IMR_EOSACC (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (TWI_IMR) End Of Slave Access Interrupt Mask */
06406 /* -------- TWI_RHR : (TWI Offset: 0x30) Receive Holding Register -------- */
06407 #define TWI_RHR_RXDATA_Pos 0
06408 #define TWI_RHR_RXDATA_Msk (0xffu << TWI_RHR_RXDATA_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_RHR) Master or Slave Receive Holding Data */
06409 /* -------- TWI_THR : (TWI Offset: 0x34) Transmit Holding Register -------- */
06410 #define TWI_THR_TXDATA_Pos 0
06411 #define TWI_THR_TXDATA_Msk (0xffu << TWI_THR_TXDATA_Pos) /**< \brief (TWI_THR) Master or Slave Transmit Holding Data */
06412 #define TWI_THR_TXDATA(value) ((TWI_THR_TXDATA_Msk & ((value) << TWI_THR_TXDATA_Pos)))
06413 
06414 /*@}*/

06416 /* ============================================================================= */
06417 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Universal Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter */
06418 /* ============================================================================= */
06419 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_UART Universal Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter */
06420 /*@{*/
06421 
06422 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
06423 /** \brief Uart hardware registers */
06424 typedef struct {
06425   WoReg UART_CR;   /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0000) Control Register */
06426   RwReg UART_MR;   /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register */
06427   WoReg UART_IER;  /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register */
06428   WoReg UART_IDR;  /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register */
06429   RoReg UART_IMR;  /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0010) Interrupt Mask Register */
06430   RoReg UART_SR;   /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0014) Status Register */
06431   RoReg UART_RHR;  /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0018) Receive Holding Register */
06432   WoReg UART_THR;  /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x001C) Transmit Holding Register */
06433   RwReg UART_BRGR; /**< \brief (Uart Offset: 0x0020) Baud Rate Generator Register */
06434 } Uart;
06435 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
06436 /* -------- UART_CR : (UART Offset: 0x0000) Control Register -------- */
06437 #define UART_CR_RSTRX (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Reset Receiver */
06438 #define UART_CR_RSTTX (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Reset Transmitter */
06439 #define UART_CR_RXEN (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Receiver Enable */
06440 #define UART_CR_RXDIS (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Receiver Disable */
06441 #define UART_CR_TXEN (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Transmitter Enable */
06442 #define UART_CR_TXDIS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Transmitter Disable */
06443 #define UART_CR_RSTSTA (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (UART_CR) Reset Status Bits */
06444 /* -------- UART_MR : (UART Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register -------- */
06445 #define UART_MR_PAR_Pos 9
06446 #define UART_MR_PAR_Msk (0x7u << UART_MR_PAR_Pos) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Parity Type */
06447 #define   UART_MR_PAR_EVEN (0x0u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Even parity */
06448 #define   UART_MR_PAR_ODD (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Odd parity */
06449 #define   UART_MR_PAR_SPACE (0x2u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Space: parity forced to 0 */
06450 #define   UART_MR_PAR_MARK (0x3u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Mark: parity forced to 1 */
06451 #define   UART_MR_PAR_NO (0x4u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_MR) No parity */
06452 #define UART_MR_CHMODE_Pos 14
06453 #define UART_MR_CHMODE_Msk (0x3u << UART_MR_CHMODE_Pos) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Channel Mode */
06454 #define   UART_MR_CHMODE_NORMAL (0x0u << 14) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Normal Mode */
06455 #define   UART_MR_CHMODE_AUTOMATIC (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Automatic Echo */
06456 #define   UART_MR_CHMODE_LOCAL_LOOPBACK (0x2u << 14) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Local Loopback */
06457 #define   UART_MR_CHMODE_REMOTE_LOOPBACK (0x3u << 14) /**< \brief (UART_MR) Remote Loopback */
06458 /* -------- UART_IER : (UART Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
06459 #define UART_IER_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable RXRDY Interrupt */
06460 #define UART_IER_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable TXRDY Interrupt */
06461 #define UART_IER_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable Overrun Error Interrupt */
06462 #define UART_IER_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable Framing Error Interrupt */
06463 #define UART_IER_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable Parity Error Interrupt */
06464 #define UART_IER_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_IER) Enable TXEMPTY Interrupt */
06465 /* -------- UART_IDR : (UART Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
06466 #define UART_IDR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable RXRDY Interrupt */
06467 #define UART_IDR_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable TXRDY Interrupt */
06468 #define UART_IDR_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable Overrun Error Interrupt */
06469 #define UART_IDR_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable Framing Error Interrupt */
06470 #define UART_IDR_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable Parity Error Interrupt */
06471 #define UART_IDR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_IDR) Disable TXEMPTY Interrupt */
06472 /* -------- UART_IMR : (UART Offset: 0x0010) Interrupt Mask Register -------- */
06473 #define UART_IMR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Mask RXRDY Interrupt */
06474 #define UART_IMR_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Disable TXRDY Interrupt */
06475 #define UART_IMR_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Mask Overrun Error Interrupt */
06476 #define UART_IMR_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Mask Framing Error Interrupt */
06477 #define UART_IMR_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Mask Parity Error Interrupt */
06478 #define UART_IMR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_IMR) Mask TXEMPTY Interrupt */
06479 /* -------- UART_SR : (UART Offset: 0x0014) Status Register -------- */
06480 #define UART_SR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Receiver Ready */
06481 #define UART_SR_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Transmitter Ready */
06482 #define UART_SR_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Overrun Error */
06483 #define UART_SR_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Framing Error */
06484 #define UART_SR_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Parity Error */
06485 #define UART_SR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UART_SR) Transmitter Empty */
06486 /* -------- UART_RHR : (UART Offset: 0x0018) Receive Holding Register -------- */
06487 #define UART_RHR_RXCHR_Pos 0
06488 #define UART_RHR_RXCHR_Msk (0xffu << UART_RHR_RXCHR_Pos) /**< \brief (UART_RHR) Received Character */
06489 /* -------- UART_THR : (UART Offset: 0x001C) Transmit Holding Register -------- */
06490 #define UART_THR_TXCHR_Pos 0
06491 #define UART_THR_TXCHR_Msk (0xffu << UART_THR_TXCHR_Pos) /**< \brief (UART_THR) Character to be Transmitted */
06492 #define UART_THR_TXCHR(value) ((UART_THR_TXCHR_Msk & ((value) << UART_THR_TXCHR_Pos)))
06493 /* -------- UART_BRGR : (UART Offset: 0x0020) Baud Rate Generator Register -------- */
06494 #define UART_BRGR_CD_Pos 0
06495 #define UART_BRGR_CD_Msk (0xffffu << UART_BRGR_CD_Pos) /**< \brief (UART_BRGR) Clock Divisor */
06496 #define UART_BRGR_CD(value) ((UART_BRGR_CD_Msk & ((value) << UART_BRGR_CD_Pos)))
06497 
06498 /*@}*/

06506 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
06507 /** \brief UdphsDma hardware registers */
06508 typedef struct {

06510   RwReg     UDPHS_DMAADDRESS; /**< \brief (UdphsDma Offset: 0x4) UDPHS DMA Channel Address Register */
06511   RwReg     UDPHS_DMACONTROL; /**< \brief (UdphsDma Offset: 0x8) UDPHS DMA Channel Control Register */
06512   RwReg     UDPHS_DMASTATUS;  /**< \brief (UdphsDma Offset: 0xC) UDPHS DMA Channel Status Register */
06513 } UdphsDma;
06514 /** \brief UdphsEpt hardware registers */
06515 typedef struct {
06516   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTCFG;     /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x0) UDPHS Endpoint Configuration Register */
06517   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTCTLENB;  /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x4) UDPHS Endpoint Control Enable Register */
06518   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTCTLDIS;  /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x8) UDPHS Endpoint Control Disable Register */
06519   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTCTL;     /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0xC) UDPHS Endpoint Control Register */
06520   RoReg     Reserved1[1];
06521   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTSETSTA;  /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x14) UDPHS Endpoint Set Status Register */
06522   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTCLRSTA;  /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x18) UDPHS Endpoint Clear Status Register */
06523   RwReg     UDPHS_EPTSTA;     /**< \brief (UdphsEpt Offset: 0x1C) UDPHS Endpoint Status Register */
06524 } UdphsEpt;
06525 /** \brief Udphs hardware registers */
06526 #define UDPHSEPT_NUMBER 7
06527 #define UDPHSDMA_NUMBER 6
06528 typedef struct {
06529   RwReg     UDPHS_CTRL;       /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x00) UDPHS Control Register */
06530   RoReg     UDPHS_FNUM;       /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x04) UDPHS Frame Number Register */
06531   RoReg     Reserved1[2];
06532   RwReg     UDPHS_IEN;        /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x10) UDPHS Interrupt Enable Register */
06533   RoReg     UDPHS_INTSTA;     /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x14) UDPHS Interrupt Status Register */
06534   WoReg     UDPHS_CLRINT;     /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x18) UDPHS Clear Interrupt Register */
06535   WoReg     UDPHS_EPTRST;     /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x1C) UDPHS Endpoints Reset Register */
06536   RoReg     Reserved2[48];
06537   RwReg     UDPHS_TST;        /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0xE0) UDPHS Test Register */
06538   RoReg     Reserved3[3];
06539   RoReg     UDPHS_IPNAME1;    /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0xF0) UDPHS Name1 Register */
06540   RoReg     UDPHS_IPNAME2;    /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0xF4) UDPHS Name2 Register */
06541   RoReg     UDPHS_IPFEATURES; /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0xF8) UDPHS Features Register */
06542   RoReg     Reserved4[1];
06543   UdphsEpt  UDPHS_EPT[UDPHSEPT_NUMBER]; /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x100) endpoint = 0 .. 6 */
06544   RoReg     Reserved5[72];
06545   UdphsDma  UDPHS_DMA[UDPHSDMA_NUMBER]; /**< \brief (Udphs Offset: 0x300) channel = 0 .. 5 */
06546 } Udphs;
06547 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
06548 /* -------- UDPHS_CTRL : (UDPHS Offset: 0x00) UDPHS Control Register -------- */
06549 #define UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR_Pos 0
06550 #define UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR_Msk (0x7fu << UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) UDPHS Address */
06551 #define UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR(value) ((UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR_Msk & ((value) << UDPHS_CTRL_DEV_ADDR_Pos)))
06552 #define UDPHS_CTRL_FADDR_EN (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) Function Address Enable */
06553 #define UDPHS_CTRL_EN_UDPHS (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) UDPHS Enable */
06554 #define UDPHS_CTRL_DETACH (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) Detach Command */
06555 #define UDPHS_CTRL_REWAKEUP (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) Send Remote Wake Up */
06556 #define UDPHS_CTRL_PULLD_DIS (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CTRL) Pull-Down Disable */
06557 /* -------- UDPHS_FNUM : (UDPHS Offset: 0x04) UDPHS Frame Number Register -------- */
06558 #define UDPHS_FNUM_MICRO_FRAME_NUM_Pos 0
06559 #define UDPHS_FNUM_MICRO_FRAME_NUM_Msk (0x7u << UDPHS_FNUM_MICRO_FRAME_NUM_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_FNUM) Microframe Number */
06560 #define UDPHS_FNUM_FRAME_NUMBER_Pos 3
06561 #define UDPHS_FNUM_FRAME_NUMBER_Msk (0x7ffu << UDPHS_FNUM_FRAME_NUMBER_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_FNUM) Frame Number as defined in the Packet Field Formats */
06562 #define UDPHS_FNUM_FNUM_ERR (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (UDPHS_FNUM) Frame Number CRC Error */
06563 /* -------- UDPHS_IEN : (UDPHS Offset: 0x10) UDPHS Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
06564 #define UDPHS_IEN_DET_SUSPD (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Suspend Interrupt Enable */
06565 #define UDPHS_IEN_MICRO_SOF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Micro-SOF Interrupt Enable */
06566 #define UDPHS_IEN_INT_SOF (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) SOF Interrupt Enable */
06567 #define UDPHS_IEN_ENDRESET (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) End Of Reset Interrupt Enable */
06568 #define UDPHS_IEN_WAKE_UP (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Wake Up CPU Interrupt Enable */
06569 #define UDPHS_IEN_ENDOFRSM (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) End Of Resume Interrupt Enable */
06570 #define UDPHS_IEN_UPSTR_RES (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Upstream Resume Interrupt Enable */
06571 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_0 (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 0 Interrupt Enable */
06572 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 1 Interrupt Enable */
06573 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_2 (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 2 Interrupt Enable */
06574 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_3 (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 3 Interrupt Enable */
06575 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_4 (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 4 Interrupt Enable */
06576 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_5 (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 5 Interrupt Enable */
06577 #define UDPHS_IEN_EPT_6 (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) Endpoint 6 Interrupt Enable */
06578 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_1 (0x1u << 25) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 1 Interrupt Enable */
06579 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_2 (0x1u << 26) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 2 Interrupt Enable */
06580 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_3 (0x1u << 27) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 3 Interrupt Enable */
06581 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_4 (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 4 Interrupt Enable */
06582 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_5 (0x1u << 29) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 5 Interrupt Enable */
06583 #define UDPHS_IEN_DMA_6 (0x1u << 30) /**< \brief (UDPHS_IEN) DMA Channel 6 Interrupt Enable */
06584 /* -------- UDPHS_INTSTA : (UDPHS Offset: 0x14) UDPHS Interrupt Status Register -------- */
06585 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_SPEED (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Speed Status */
06586 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DET_SUSPD (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Suspend Interrupt */
06587 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_MICRO_SOF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Micro Start Of Frame Interrupt */
06588 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_INT_SOF (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Start Of Frame Interrupt */
06589 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_ENDRESET (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) End Of Reset Interrupt */
06590 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_WAKE_UP (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Wake Up CPU Interrupt */
06591 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_ENDOFRSM (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) End Of Resume Interrupt */
06592 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_UPSTR_RES (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Upstream Resume Interrupt */
06593 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_0 (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 0 Interrupt */
06594 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_1 (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 1 Interrupt */
06595 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_2 (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 2 Interrupt */
06596 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_3 (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 3 Interrupt */
06597 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_4 (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 4 Interrupt */
06598 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_5 (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 5 Interrupt */
06599 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_EPT_6 (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) Endpoint 6 Interrupt */
06600 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_1 (0x1u << 25) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 1 Interrupt */
06601 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_2 (0x1u << 26) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 2 Interrupt */
06602 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_3 (0x1u << 27) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 3 Interrupt */
06603 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_4 (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 4 Interrupt */
06604 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_5 (0x1u << 29) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 5 Interrupt */
06605 #define UDPHS_INTSTA_DMA_6 (0x1u << 30) /**< \brief (UDPHS_INTSTA) DMA Channel 6 Interrupt */
06606 /* -------- UDPHS_CLRINT : (UDPHS Offset: 0x18) UDPHS Clear Interrupt Register -------- */
06607 #define UDPHS_CLRINT_DET_SUSPD (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CLRINT) Suspend Interrupt Clear */
06608 #define UDPHS_CLRINT_MICRO_SOF (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CLRINT) Micro Start Of Frame Interrupt Clear */
06609 #define UDPHS_CLRINT_INT_SOF (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UDPHS_CLRINT) Start Of Frame Interrupt Clear */

06623 #define UDPHS_TST_SPEED_CFG_Pos 0

06625 #define   UDPHS_TST_SPEED_CFG_NORMAL (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_TST) Normal Mode: The macro is in Full Speed mode, ready to make a High Speed identification, if the host supports it and then to automatically switch to High Speed mode */
06626 #define   UDPHS_TST_SPEED_CFG_HIGH_SPEED (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_TST) Force High Speed: Set this value to force the hardware to work in High Speed mode. Only for debug or test purpose. */
06627 #define   UDPHS_TST_SPEED_CFG_FULL_SPEED (0x3u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_TST) Force Full Speed: Set this value to force the hardware to work only in Full Speed mode. In this configuration, the macro will not respond to a High Speed reset handshake. */
06628 #define UDPHS_TST_TST_J (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UDPHS_TST) Test J Mode */
06629 #define UDPHS_TST_TST_K (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UDPHS_TST) Test K Mode */

06774 #define UDPHS_EPTCLRSTA_NAK_OUT (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTCLRSTA) NAKOUT Clear */
06775 /* -------- UDPHS_EPTSTA : (UDPHS Offset: N/A) UDPHS Endpoint Status Register -------- */
06776 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_FRCESTALL (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Stall Handshake Request */
06777 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_Pos 6
06778 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_Msk (0x3u << UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Toggle Sequencing */
06779 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_DATA0 (0x0u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) DATA0 */
06780 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_DATA1 (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) DATA1 */
06781 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_DATA2 (0x2u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Data2 (only for High Bandwidth Isochronous Endpoint) */
06782 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_TOGGLESQ_STA_MDATA (0x3u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) MData (only for High Bandwidth Isochronous Endpoint) */
06783 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_OVFLW (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Overflow Error */
06784 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_RX_BK_RDY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Received OUT Data/KILL Bank */
06785 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_KILL_BANK (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Received OUT Data/KILL Bank */
06786 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_TX_COMPLT (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Transmitted IN Data Complete */
06787 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_TX_PK_RDY (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) TX Packet Ready/Transaction Error */
06788 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_TRANS (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) TX Packet Ready/Transaction Error */
06789 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_RX_SETUP (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Received SETUP/Error Flow */
06790 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_FL_ISO (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Received SETUP/Error Flow */
06791 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_STALL_SNT (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Stall Sent/CRC ISO Error/Number of Transaction Error */
06792 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_CRISO (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Stall Sent/CRC ISO Error/Number of Transaction Error */
06793 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_NBTRA (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Stall Sent/CRC ISO Error/Number of Transaction Error */
06794 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_NAK_IN (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) NAK IN/Bank Flush Error */
06795 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_ERR_FLUSH (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) NAK IN/Bank Flush Error */
06796 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_NAK_OUT (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) NAK OUT */
06797 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_CURRENT_BANK_Pos 16
06798 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_CURRENT_BANK_Msk (0x3u << UDPHS_EPTSTA_CURRENT_BANK_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Current Bank/Control Direction */
06799 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_CONTROL_DIR_Pos 16
06800 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_CONTROL_DIR_Msk (0x3u << UDPHS_EPTSTA_CONTROL_DIR_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Current Bank/Control Direction */
06801 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_Pos 18
06802 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_Msk (0x3u << UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Busy Bank Number */
06803 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_1BUSYBANK (0x0u << 18) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) 1 busy bank */
06804 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_2BUSYBANKS (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) 2 busy banks */
06805 #define   UDPHS_EPTSTA_BUSY_BANK_STA_3BUSYBANKS (0x2u << 18) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) 3 busy banks */
06806 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_BYTE_COUNT_Pos 20
06807 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_BYTE_COUNT_Msk (0x7ffu << UDPHS_EPTSTA_BYTE_COUNT_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) UDPHS Byte Count */
06808 #define UDPHS_EPTSTA_SHRT_PCKT (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (UDPHS_EPTSTA) Short Packet */
06809 /* -------- UDPHS_DMANXTDSC : (UDPHS Offset: N/A) UDPHS DMA Next Descriptor Address Register -------- */
06810 #define UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD_Pos 0
06811 #define UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD_Msk (0xffffffffu << UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMANXTDSC)  */
06812 #define UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD(value) ((UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD_Msk & ((value) << UDPHS_DMANXTDSC_NXT_DSC_ADD_Pos)))
06813 /* -------- UDPHS_DMAADDRESS : (UDPHS Offset: N/A) UDPHS DMA Channel Address Register -------- */
06814 #define UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD_Pos 0
06815 #define UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD_Msk (0xffffffffu << UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMAADDRESS)  */
06816 #define UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD(value) ((UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD_Msk & ((value) << UDPHS_DMAADDRESS_BUFF_ADD_Pos)))
06817 /* -------- UDPHS_DMACONTROL : (UDPHS Offset: N/A) UDPHS DMA Channel Control Register -------- */
06818 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_CHANN_ENB (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL)  */
06819 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_LDNXT_DSC (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) Load Next Channel Transfer Descriptor Enable (Command) */
06820 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_END_TR_EN (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) End of Transfer Enable (Control) */
06821 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_END_B_EN (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) End of Buffer Enable (Control) */
06822 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_END_TR_IT (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) End of Transfer Interrupt Enable */
06823 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_END_BUFFIT (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) End of Buffer Interrupt Enable */
06824 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_DESC_LD_IT (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) Descriptor Loaded Interrupt Enable */
06825 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BURST_LCK (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) Burst Lock Enable */
06826 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH_Pos 16
06827 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH_Msk (0xffffu << UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMACONTROL) Buffer Byte Length (Write-only) */
06828 #define UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH(value) ((UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH_Msk & ((value) << UDPHS_DMACONTROL_BUFF_LENGTH_Pos)))
06829 /* -------- UDPHS_DMASTATUS : (UDPHS Offset: N/A) UDPHS DMA Channel Status Register -------- */
06830 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_CHANN_ENB (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) Channel Enable Status */
06831 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_CHANN_ACT (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) Channel Active Status */
06832 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_END_TR_ST (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) End of Channel Transfer Status */
06833 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_END_BF_ST (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) End of Channel Buffer Status */
06834 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_DESC_LDST (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) Descriptor Loaded Status */
06835 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT_Pos 16
06836 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT_Msk (0xffffu << UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT_Pos) /**< \brief (UDPHS_DMASTATUS) Buffer Byte Count */
06837 #define UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT(value) ((UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT_Msk & ((value) << UDPHS_DMASTATUS_BUFF_COUNT_Pos)))
06838

06842 /**  SOFTWARE API DEFINITION FOR Universal Synchronous Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter */

06844 /** \addtogroup AT91SAM9G15_USART Universal Synchronous Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter */
06845 /*@{*/
06846 
06847 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
06848 /** \brief Usart hardware registers */
06849 typedef struct {
06850   WoReg US_CR;         /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0000) Control Register */
06851   RwReg US_MR;         /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register */
06852   WoReg US_IER;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register */
06853   WoReg US_IDR;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register */
06854   RoReg US_IMR;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0010) Interrupt Mask Register */
06855   RoReg US_CSR;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0014) Channel Status Register */
06856   RoReg US_RHR;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0018) Receiver Holding Register */
06857   WoReg US_THR;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x001C) Transmitter Holding Register */
06858   RwReg US_BRGR;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0020) Baud Rate Generator Register */
06859   RwReg US_RTOR;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0024) Receiver Time-out Register */
06860   RwReg US_TTGR;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0028) Transmitter Timeguard Register */
06861   RoReg Reserved1[5];
06862   RwReg US_FIDI;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0040) FI DI Ratio Register */
06863   RoReg US_NER;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0044) Number of Errors Register */
06864   RoReg Reserved2[1];
06865   RwReg US_IF;         /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x004C) IrDA Filter Register */
06866   RwReg US_MAN;        /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0050) Manchester Encoder Decoder Register */
06867   RwReg US_LINMR;      /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0054) LIN Mode Register */
06868   RwReg US_LINIR;      /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0x0058) LIN Identifier Register */
06869   RoReg Reserved3[34];
06870   RwReg US_WPMR;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0xE4) Write Protect Mode Register */
06871   RoReg US_WPSR;       /**< \brief (Usart Offset: 0xE8) Write Protect Status Register */
06872 } Usart;
06873 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
06874 /* -------- US_CR : (USART Offset: 0x0000) Control Register -------- */
06875 #define US_CR_RSTRX (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (US_CR) Reset Receiver */
06876 #define US_CR_RSTTX (0x1u << 3) /**< \brief (US_CR) Reset Transmitter */
06877 #define US_CR_RXEN (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (US_CR) Receiver Enable */
06878 #define US_CR_RXDIS (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (US_CR) Receiver Disable */
06879 #define US_CR_TXEN (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (US_CR) Transmitter Enable */
06880 #define US_CR_TXDIS (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (US_CR) Transmitter Disable */
06881 #define US_CR_RSTSTA (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (US_CR) Reset Status Bits */
06882 #define US_CR_STTBRK (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (US_CR) Start Break */
06883 #define US_CR_STPBRK (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (US_CR) Stop Break */
06884 #define US_CR_STTTO (0x1u << 11) /**< \brief (US_CR) Start Time-out */
06885 #define US_CR_SENDA (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (US_CR) Send Address */
06886 #define US_CR_RSTIT (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (US_CR) Reset Iterations */
06887 #define US_CR_RSTNACK (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (US_CR) Reset Non Acknowledge */
06888 #define US_CR_RETTO (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (US_CR) Rearm Time-out */
06889 #define US_CR_RTSEN (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (US_CR) Request to Send Enable */
06890 #define US_CR_FCS (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (US_CR) Force SPI Chip Select */
06891 #define US_CR_RTSDIS (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (US_CR) Request to Send Disable */
06892 #define US_CR_RCS (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (US_CR) Release SPI Chip Select */
06893 #define US_CR_LINABT (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (US_CR) Abort LIN Transmission */
06894 #define US_CR_LINWKUP (0x1u << 21) /**< \brief (US_CR) Send LIN Wakeup Signal */
06895 /* -------- US_MR : (USART Offset: 0x0004) Mode Register -------- */
06896 #define US_MR_USART_MODE_Pos 0
06897 #define US_MR_USART_MODE_Msk (0xfu << US_MR_USART_MODE_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR)  */
06898 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_NORMAL (0x0u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) Normal mode */
06899 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_RS485 (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) RS485 */
06900 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_HW_HANDSHAKING (0x2u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) Hardware Handshaking */
06901 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_IS07816_T_0 (0x4u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) IS07816 Protocol: T = 0 */
06902 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_IS07816_T_1 (0x6u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) IS07816 Protocol: T = 1 */
06903 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_IRDA (0x8u << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) IrDA */
06904 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_LIN_MASTER (0xAu << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) LIN Master */
06905 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_LIN_SLAVE (0xBu << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) LIN Slave */
06906 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_SPI_MASTER (0xEu << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) SPI Master */
06907 #define   US_MR_USART_MODE_SPI_SLAVE (0xFu << 0) /**< \brief (US_MR) SPI Slave */
06908 #define US_MR_USCLKS_Pos 4
06909 #define US_MR_USCLKS_Msk (0x3u << US_MR_USCLKS_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR) Clock Selection */
06910 #define   US_MR_USCLKS_MCK (0x0u << 4) /**< \brief (US_MR) Master Clock MCK is selected */
06911 #define   US_MR_USCLKS_DIV (0x1u << 4) /**< \brief (US_MR) Internal Clock Divided MCK/DIV (DIV=8) is selected */
06912 #define   US_MR_USCLKS_SCK (0x3u << 4) /**< \brief (US_MR) Serial Clock SLK is selected */
06913 #define US_MR_CHRL_Pos 6
06914 #define US_MR_CHRL_Msk (0x3u << US_MR_CHRL_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR) Character Length. */
06915 #define   US_MR_CHRL_5_BIT (0x0u << 6) /**< \brief (US_MR) Character length is 5 bits */
06916 #define   US_MR_CHRL_6_BIT (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (US_MR) Character length is 6 bits */
06917 #define   US_MR_CHRL_7_BIT (0x2u << 6) /**< \brief (US_MR) Character length is 7 bits */
06918 #define   US_MR_CHRL_8_BIT (0x3u << 6) /**< \brief (US_MR) Character length is 8 bits */
06919 #define US_MR_SYNC (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (US_MR) Synchronous Mode Select */
06920 #define US_MR_CPHA (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (US_MR) SPI Clock Phase */
06921 #define US_MR_PAR_Pos 9
06922 #define US_MR_PAR_Msk (0x7u << US_MR_PAR_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR) Parity Type */
06923 #define   US_MR_PAR_EVEN (0x0u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) Even parity */
06924 #define   US_MR_PAR_ODD (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) Odd parity */
06925 #define   US_MR_PAR_SPACE (0x2u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) Parity forced to 0 (Space) */
06926 #define   US_MR_PAR_MARK (0x3u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) Parity forced to 1 (Mark) */
06927 #define   US_MR_PAR_NO (0x4u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) No parity */
06928 #define   US_MR_PAR_MULTIDROP (0x6u << 9) /**< \brief (US_MR) Multidrop mode */
06929 #define US_MR_NBSTOP_Pos 12
06930 #define US_MR_NBSTOP_Msk (0x3u << US_MR_NBSTOP_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR) Number of Stop Bits */
06931 #define   US_MR_NBSTOP_1_BIT (0x0u << 12) /**< \brief (US_MR) 1 stop bit */
06932 #define   US_MR_NBSTOP_1_5_BIT (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (US_MR) 1.5 stop bit (SYNC = 0) or reserved (SYNC = 1) */
06933 #define   US_MR_NBSTOP_2_BIT (0x2u << 12) /**< \brief (US_MR) 2 stop bits */
06934 #define US_MR_CHMODE_Pos 14
06935 #define US_MR_CHMODE_Msk (0x3u << US_MR_CHMODE_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR) Channel Mode */
06936 #define   US_MR_CHMODE_NORMAL (0x0u << 14) /**< \brief (US_MR) Normal Mode */
06937 #define   US_MR_CHMODE_AUTOMATIC (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (US_MR) Automatic Echo. Receiver input is connected to the TXD pin. */
06938 #define   US_MR_CHMODE_LOCAL_LOOPBACK (0x2u << 14) /**< \brief (US_MR) Local Loopback. Transmitter output is connected to the Receiver Input. */
06939 #define   US_MR_CHMODE_REMOTE_LOOPBACK (0x3u << 14) /**< \brief (US_MR) Remote Loopback. RXD pin is internally connected to the TXD pin. */
06940 #define US_MR_MSBF (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (US_MR) Bit Order */
06941 #define US_MR_CPOL (0x1u << 16) /**< \brief (US_MR) SPI Clock Polarity */
06942 #define US_MR_MODE9 (0x1u << 17) /**< \brief (US_MR) 9-bit Character Length */
06943 #define US_MR_CLKO (0x1u << 18) /**< \brief (US_MR) Clock Output Select */
06944 #define US_MR_OVER (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (US_MR) Oversampling Mode */
06945 #define US_MR_INACK (0x1u << 20) /**< \brief (US_MR) Inhibit Non Acknowledge */
06946 #define US_MR_DSNACK (0x1u << 21) /**< \brief (US_MR) Disable Successive NACK */
06947 #define US_MR_VAR_SYNC (0x1u << 22) /**< \brief (US_MR) Variable Synchronization of Command/Data Sync Start Frame Delimiter */
06948 #define US_MR_MAX_ITERATION_Pos 24
06949 #define US_MR_MAX_ITERATION_Msk (0x7u << US_MR_MAX_ITERATION_Pos) /**< \brief (US_MR)  */
06950 #define US_MR_MAX_ITERATION(value) ((US_MR_MAX_ITERATION_Msk & ((value) << US_MR_MAX_ITERATION_Pos)))
06951 #define US_MR_FILTER (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (US_MR) Infrared Receive Line Filter */
06952 #define US_MR_MAN (0x1u << 29) /**< \brief (US_MR) Manchester Encoder/Decoder Enable */
06953 #define US_MR_MODSYNC (0x1u << 30) /**< \brief (US_MR) Manchester Synchronization Mode */
06954 #define US_MR_ONEBIT (0x1u << 31) /**< \brief (US_MR) Start Frame Delimiter Selector */
06955 /* -------- US_IER : (USART Offset: 0x0008) Interrupt Enable Register -------- */
06956 #define US_IER_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (US_IER) RXRDY Interrupt Enable */
06957 #define US_IER_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (US_IER) TXRDY Interrupt Enable */
06958 #define US_IER_RXBRK (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (US_IER) Receiver Break Interrupt Enable */
06959 #define US_IER_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (US_IER) Overrun Error Interrupt Enable */
06960 #define US_IER_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (US_IER) Framing Error Interrupt Enable */
06961 #define US_IER_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (US_IER) Parity Error Interrupt Enable */
06962 #define US_IER_TIMEOUT (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (US_IER) Time-out Interrupt Enable */
06963 #define US_IER_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (US_IER) TXEMPTY Interrupt Enable */
06964 #define US_IER_ITER (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (US_IER) Max number of Repetitions Reached */
06965 #define US_IER_UNRE (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (US_IER) SPI Underrun Error */
06966 #define US_IER_NACK (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (US_IER) Non Acknowledge Interrupt Enable */
06967 #define US_IER_LINBK (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Break Sent or LIN Break Received Interrupt Enable */
06968 #define US_IER_LINID (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Identifier Sent or LIN Identifier Received Interrupt Enable */
06969 #define US_IER_LINTC (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Transfer Completed Interrupt Enable */
06970 #define US_IER_CTSIC (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (US_IER) Clear to Send Input Change Interrupt Enable */
06971 #define US_IER_MANE (0x1u << 24) /**< \brief (US_IER) Manchester Error Interrupt Enable */
06972 #define US_IER_LINBE (0x1u << 25) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Bus Error Interrupt Enable */
06973 #define US_IER_LINISFE (0x1u << 26) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Inconsistent Synch Field Error Interrupt Enable */
06974 #define US_IER_LINIPE (0x1u << 27) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Identifier Parity Interrupt Enable */
06975 #define US_IER_LINCE (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Checksum Error Interrupt Enable */
06976 #define US_IER_LINSNRE (0x1u << 29) /**< \brief (US_IER) LIN Slave Not Responding Error Interrupt Enable */
06977 /* -------- US_IDR : (USART Offset: 0x000C) Interrupt Disable Register -------- */
06978 #define US_IDR_RXRDY (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (US_IDR) RXRDY Interrupt Disable */
06979 #define US_IDR_TXRDY (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (US_IDR) TXRDY Interrupt Disable */
06980 #define US_IDR_RXBRK (0x1u << 2) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Receiver Break Interrupt Disable */
06981 #define US_IDR_OVRE (0x1u << 5) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Overrun Error Interrupt Disable */
06982 #define US_IDR_FRAME (0x1u << 6) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Framing Error Interrupt Disable */
06983 #define US_IDR_PARE (0x1u << 7) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Parity Error Interrupt Disable */
06984 #define US_IDR_TIMEOUT (0x1u << 8) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Time-out Interrupt Disable */
06985 #define US_IDR_TXEMPTY (0x1u << 9) /**< \brief (US_IDR) TXEMPTY Interrupt Disable */
06986 #define US_IDR_ITER (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Max number of Repetitions Reached Disable */
06987 #define US_IDR_UNRE (0x1u << 10) /**< \brief (US_IDR) SPI Underrun Error Disable */
06988 #define US_IDR_NACK (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Non Acknowledge Interrupt Disable */
06989 #define US_IDR_LINBK (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (US_IDR) LIN Break Sent or LIN Break Received Interrupt Disable */
06990 #define US_IDR_LINID (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (US_IDR) LIN Identifier Sent or LIN Identifier Received Interrupt Disable */
06991 #define US_IDR_LINTC (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (US_IDR) LIN Transfer Completed Interrupt Disable */
06992 #define US_IDR_CTSIC (0x1u << 19) /**< \brief (US_IDR) Clear to Send Input Change Interrupt Disable */

07141 #ifndef __ASSEMBLY__
07142 /** \brief Wdt hardware registers */
07143 typedef struct {
07144   WoReg WDT_CR; /**< \brief (Wdt Offset: 0x00) Control Register */

07147 } Wdt;
07148 #endif /* __ASSEMBLY__ */
07149 /* -------- WDT_CR : (WDT Offset: 0x00) Control Register -------- */
07150 #define WDT_CR_WDRSTT (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (WDT_CR) Watchdog Restart */
07151 #define WDT_CR_KEY_Pos 24
07152 #define WDT_CR_KEY_Msk (0xffu << WDT_CR_KEY_Pos) /**< \brief (WDT_CR) Password */
07153 #define WDT_CR_KEY(value) ((WDT_CR_KEY_Msk & ((value) << WDT_CR_KEY_Pos)))
07154 /* -------- WDT_MR : (WDT Offset: 0x04) Mode Register -------- */
07155 #define WDT_MR_WDV_Pos 0
07156 #define WDT_MR_WDV_Msk (0xfffu << WDT_MR_WDV_Pos) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Counter Value */
07157 #define WDT_MR_WDV(value) ((WDT_MR_WDV_Msk & ((value) << WDT_MR_WDV_Pos)))
07158 #define WDT_MR_WDFIEN (0x1u << 12) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Fault Interrupt Enable */
07159 #define WDT_MR_WDRSTEN (0x1u << 13) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Reset Enable */
07160 #define WDT_MR_WDRPROC (0x1u << 14) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Reset Processor */
07161 #define WDT_MR_WDDIS (0x1u << 15) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Disable */
07162 #define WDT_MR_WDD_Pos 16
07163 #define WDT_MR_WDD_Msk (0xfffu << WDT_MR_WDD_Pos) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Delta Value */
07164 #define WDT_MR_WDD(value) ((WDT_MR_WDD_Msk & ((value) << WDT_MR_WDD_Pos)))
07165 #define WDT_MR_WDDBGHLT (0x1u << 28) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Debug Halt */
07166 #define WDT_MR_WDIDLEHLT (0x1u << 29) /**< \brief (WDT_MR) Watchdog Idle Halt */
07167 /* -------- WDT_SR : (WDT Offset: 0x08) Status Register -------- */
07168 #define WDT_SR_WDUNF (0x1u << 0) /**< \brief (WDT_SR) Watchdog Underflow */
07169 #define WDT_SR_WDERR (0x1u << 1) /**< \brief (WDT_SR) Watchdog Error */
